title: chocolate bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat; add chocolate bars and stir, mixing well.
Let cool. Whip cream and fold in.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not drain crab meat.
Yields 20 to 30 servings.

title: coconut shrimp with sweet dipping sauce
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, beer and next 5 ingredients. Dredge shrimp in remaining 1/2 cup flour; dip in beer batter and roll in coconut. Fry shrimp in deep hot oil (350°) until coconut is golden brown. Serve shrimp with Sweet Dipping Sauce. Yields 6 servings.

title: tony's easy frosting
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, vanilla and cocoa. Add milk small amounts at a time until smooth.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach and combine with next three ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Hollow out center of bread loaf; keeping pieces.
Fill with dip and chill.
Serve with vegetables and bread pieces.

title: apple loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 5 ingredients together well. Then in a large bowl beat butter, sugar and 1 egg until smooth. Beat in second egg, stir in vanilla, then apples. Pour flour mixture into batter. Mix until moist. Pour into greased 9x5 inch pan. Bake 1 hr.

title: garlic home fries
directions: Boil diced potatoes, with skins left on, in water until done. Drain and set aside.
In skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add drained potatoes.
Sprinkle generously with paprika. Cook until crisp on all sides.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Beat with electric mixer until well mixed.
Form into ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and cut in 1-inch thick chunks.
Melt butter and marmalade.
Add 1/4 cup of brown sugar and 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Pour 1/3 of this mixture into baking dish.
Add sweet potatoes and pineapple chunks together.
Sprinkle remaining brown sugar over top of potatoes.
Pour remaining syrup over potatoes.
Put in 400° oven until it bubbles.

title: spinach elegante
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain well.
Spread on bottom of 10 x 6 x
1 1/2-inch pan.
Arrange bacon and mushrooms over spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and marjoram.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cover with sour cream and cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Remove and add the butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Add the soda; stir quickly and pour into a cookie sheet.
Spread thin.

title: rosey adams' fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs; beat well. Add baking powder to 1 cup of flour.
Mix well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Mix the other cup of flour with the fruit. Add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Line pan with well-greased brown paper.
Pour into pan.
Place in cold oven; bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: escalloped chicken with dressing
directions: Cook celery and green pepper in oleo until partially cooked. Add flour and cook 5 minutes.
Add broth and milk; cook until thick.
Add seasonings and pimento.
Set aside and prepare dressing.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine eggs and salad oil. Beat on high speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Blend in sugar. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add to other mixture. Mix well. Stir in apples and nuts. Mix again. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Combine yeast in bowl.
Add warm water, sugar, salt and egg. Add shortening and flour.
Let rise 2 hours, then put in icebox. Make out and let rise and cook as needed.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash, gently dry and remove stems from mushrooms or use drained whole mushroom caps.
Fill with one of the following: tuna salad, chicken or turkey salad, ham salad, cheese salad, egg salad or cottage cheese salad.

title: j j's special salsa
directions: With food processor or by hand, chop fine (do not blend) the cilantro, green onions, jalapeno peppers and green chilies.
Mix in bowl.
Slice the tomatoes; add to mix.
Mix tomato sauce and water; add to mixture.
Cut up fresh tomatoes into desired chunks; stir into mixture.
Will keep up to 7 days under refrigeration.

title: prune and apricot upside-down cake
directions: Blend the butter and brown sugar; add lemon rind. Spread in bottom of cake pan, about 8-inches square and 2-inches deep. Arrange apricot and prune halves to form a design on top of sugar mixture in cake pan.

title: baked tomatoes with spinach
directions: Place tomatoes in shallow baking dish, cut side down.
Mix rest of ingredients, except crumbs.
Divide and spread evenly over tomatoes.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until crumbs are toasted and tomato heated.
Yields 6 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut up carrots; steam in baking dish.
Add brown sugar.
Pour margarine over carrots.
Bake for about 10 minutes.

title: layer nacho dip
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Spread can of refried beans in bottom of dish.
Next, place taco meat mixture, next place taco sauce (salsa).
Spread grated cheese (as mush as you like); chop green onions and olives on top of this mixture.
Place in microwave when ready to serve, until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: banana muffins with streusel topping
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of muffin cups.
Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat bananas, oil, milk, vanilla and egg.

Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, except the reserved mixture of brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Stir until moistened and divide evenly into 12 to 15 muffin cups. Sprinkle top with reserved mixture.
Bake about 20 minutes. Immediately remove from muffin cups.
"Enjoy."

title: coach fleming's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
That's all!
Store in refrigerator. Keeps indefinitely.
Best ever for spareribs.

title: carrots with orange sauce
directions: Clean, slice and cook carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over cooked carrots.
Cover and let stand at least 20 minutes.

title: raspberry mint crush
directions: Combine sugar, mint leaves and 1 cup of boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add raspberries and concentrate; stir well until thawed.
Add 2 cups cold water and stir.
Serve over ice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to box.
Meanwhile, grate the cheese and set aside.
Pour tomatoes into a medium saucepan and crush them.
Add cheese and mix together. Cook over medium-low heat until melted together nicely.
Drain macaroni well and pour into a large bowl.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni and mix well.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes a great side dish for any entree.

title: mexi-chile dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to vegetable mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: breakfast sausage and egg casserole
directions: Oil a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cube bread and line bottom of pan.
Cook and drain sausage; sprinkle over bread.
Add cheese, mushrooms, cream, milk and seasoning to eggs.
Stir and pour over bread and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: angel gingerbread(this recipe is 75 years old.)
directions: Beat egg.
Add melted shortening and set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and ginger and add to egg mixture, beating thoroughly.
Add molasses.
Dissolve soda in boiling water; add water mixture to combined ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender, take out of broth; let cool.
Then slice chicken up, cut potatoes into bite size pieces. Slice mushrooms and onions.
Take 1 can of tomatoes and one bottle of Heinz 57 sauce; place in blender to mix.
Add all ingredients to chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Good eating!!!

title: maple-glazed pork chops
directions: Trim any excess fat off pork chops.
Brown chops in oil and butter over medium heat, about 5 minutes each side.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Add bay leaf and pecans.
Continue cooking on low heat (simmer) for 10 minutes. Add maple syrup and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Turn chops.
Cook about 5 minutes longer, until sauce has thickened slightly.
Spoon sauce over chops and serve.

title: sheep herder's stew(method:  dutch oven)
directions: If beef is cooked, chop up and put in Dutch oven.
If beef is raw, brown it in Dutch oven, then add salt and pepper, diced raw potatoes, peeled and diced raw carrots, diced onion, both cans of soup and 1/2 soup can of milk.
Cover; cook until meat and vegetables are all tender, about 25 minutes.

title: soy fried rice
directions: Heat oil; add eggs, mixing constantly while breaking up with fork.
Add eggs and onions to rice with soy sauce to color rice brown.
Blend very well and serve hot.
(Can be reheated in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.)
If desired, stir in 1 cup cooked, diced shrimp or 1 cup cooked, diced pork tenderloin.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add next three ingredients.
Sprinkle pecan halves in pie shell.
Pour filling over all.
Bake for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until pie is set.

title: avocado enchiladas
directions: Place slices of avocados in center of tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up tortillas and place in pan sprayed with Pam. Pour green sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with olives and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and bread crumbs.
Melt margarine; add bread crumbs.
Line a greased casserole with half of the bread crumb mixture.
Spoon in squash mixture.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: salinas valley potato topper
directions: In a small heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine. Add broccoli. Cook and stir just until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in yogurt and Mozzarella.
To serve, spoon onto baked potato halves and sprinkle with paprika.

title: raisin nut cake
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add rest of ingredients gradually.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chalupas (aka tostadas)
directions: In a sauce pan, add beans, picante, canola oil, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat while stirring occasionally until mixture becomes blended and hot.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Fritos.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot, about 20 minutes. Remove from oven and add crushed Fritos.
Bake until Fritos are hot. Serve while hot.

title: never-fail cupcakes
directions: Put into bowl in order given.
Do not mix until last item has been added, then beat well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or so. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: party cheesecakes
directions: Place paper liners in 24 muffin tins.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour enough filling into muffin liners to fill each about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly or refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, spoon cherry pie filling on top of each cheesecake.
I like to use the very small muffin cups; these make bite size cheesecakes and also more servings.
Serves 24 people.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all together, except wieners.
Let set for 30 minutes. Dip wieners in dough mixture.
Deep fry until brown.

title: barbecue bean and bacon dip appetizers
directions: Blend well and serve with crackers, corn chips and crisp vegetables.
Serve cold.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Pour into
greased casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Melt oleo, cocoa and water. Let it come to a boil and pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a large 4-quart skillet, wok or stock pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Add the garlic and cook until lightly brown.
Immediately add the chicken and stir-fry, turning constantly, until nearly cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Add the wine and bring to a vigorous simmer.
Add carrots, cover and steam for 1 to 2 minutes.
Then in succession, add the broccoli and cauliflower together.
Stir, cover and steam for 1 to 2 minutes; then the peppers.
Stir, cover and steam.
Add the snow peas; stir, cover and steam.
Add the celery; stir, cover and steam.
If extra liquid is needed, you can add a bit more wine or water.
Be conservative, as the vegetables will begin adding their own liquid.
Add sugar, basil, tarragon and soy sauce sauce; stir. Stir in lemon juice just before serving.
Serve over hot rice with soy sauce on the side.

title: soul bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Pour in boiling water; beat with electric mixer until well mixed.
Boil sweet potato until tender; peel while hot.
Add to meal mixture; beat 10 minutes.
Add cold water; beat well.
Add flour and molasses; beat well.
Cover.
Place in warm, draft-free place overnight.

title: vegetable loaf
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Add 3 eggs, beaten into 1 can milk and 1 can water; pour over mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 2 small loaf pans or 1 large pan, greased.
Bake until brown (1 1/2 hours approximately) at 350°.
Don't overbake.

title: chocolate chip cloud cookies
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Line a large cookie sheet with butchers paper.
In large bowl, whip egg whites and tartar at high speed until foamy; beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff and glossy peaks form.
Beat in vanilla.
Gently but thoroughly, fold in chocolate chips and cocoa.
Drop by teaspoons on prepared cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake for 1 hour until outside of cookies are dry and set.
Let cool and peel off paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: mock lobster casserole
directions: Place fish in greased Pyrex dish and cover with crabmeat.
Add the bisque.
Mix crumbled crackers with margarine. Pour over fish and crabmeat.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour all this into graham cracker crust and chill for 1 hour.
Pour on cherry pie filling and top with whipped cream.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Spread sausage over bottom on 9 x 13 pan and cover with cheese. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over cheese. Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until middle is done.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts on tray in oven until light brown.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Fold in sugar and salt.
Beat until stiff peaks form. Fold nuts into meringue.
Melt butter in a jelly roll pan (or cookie sheet with sides).
Spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until no butter remains.
Stir every 10 minutes while baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar with Crisco.
Add eggs, then self-rising flour. Alternately add milk and plain flour.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed salted nuts
directions: Mix oil and syrup in saucepan.
Heat gently, then stir in nuts.
Put in iron skillet and place in a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir 4 times.
Remove and cool.
Transfer to jars or canisters with lids.

title: tuna corn casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes, 1/4 teaspoon onion powder and butter until evenly coated.
Set aside.
Combine soup, milk, 1/4 teaspoon onion powder and dill.
Stir in tuna, corn, 1/4 cup cheese, olives and 1/2 cup reserved crumb mixture.
Spoon into shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese, then remaining corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly at edges.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Slice cake in 1/2-inch slices and cover bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Put 1/2 of peach slices over cake. Mix Eagle Brand milk, water, almond extract and pudding; fold in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 of mixture over peaches. Add another layer of cake, peaches and pudding mixture. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: mushroom stuffed round steak
directions: Pound steak; sprinkle with tenderizer.
Prick with fork. Spread with butter; season.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread on steak.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Put in large shallow baking dish.
Arrange vegetables around steak.
Add 1 cup water to soup mix.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: berry-banana breakfast smoothie
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Stir until all the flour is taken up.
Drop into greased or Pam sprayed muffin cups and bake at 425° until brown.

title: maple snow(vermont style)
directions: Fill a cereal bowl with fresh fallen snow. Top with real maple syrup and eat with a spoon!

title: oat "meal" raw bran cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix in large bowl cream and sugar. Stir in oats and bran.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix them.
Let stand until it is all soaked and drop on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 12 regular sized cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar and garlic salt.
Add onion.
Combine egg and buttermilk, then add to dry ingredients. Stir until mixture is moist.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil at 400°, frying only a few at a time.
Turn hush puppies once and cook until they are golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towel.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix jelly, onion flakes and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan. Heat and stir to boiling.
Add wieners and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Keep warm over warmer candle or sterns.
Serve hot as tidbit.

title: banana butterfinger pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding mix until thickened and smooth. Set aside 1/3 cup candy bars for topping. Fold Cool Whip, bananas and remaining candy bars into pudding. Spoon into serving dishes; refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Prepare sausage and drain off fat.
Place crescent rolls together as crust in round pan or rectangular pizza pan (raw dough).
Spread hash browns, sausage and cheese over crust. Scramble/whip eggs and pour over fillings.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Can season with different spices or with salt and pepper.)
Enjoy!

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle coconut in bottom of pan. Sprinkle pecans over top of coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter over top of pecans and coconut.
In separate bowl, cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and mix until smooth.
Drop powdered sugar mixture by spoonfuls over cake (keep away from sides of pan).
Bake as directed on cake mix box plus add about 15 or 20 minutes extra baking time due to cream cheese mixture.
Allow cake to cool to touch and turn upside-down on plate.

title: chicken breasts with ham and cheese
directions: Pound each chicken breast on both sides.

Place one slice of ham and one slice of cheese on each chicken breast and fold closed. Trim the ham and cheese to fit neatly into each breast. Dip each breast in the seasoned flour, then the egg and finally the seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet. Saute breasts approximately 5 minutes on each side or until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and pour on top of cake.
I prefer Birds Eye strawberries in pouch, more color and flavor.

title: holiday spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except jelly.
Spread on a large round plate or tray.
Just before serving, spread jelly on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together for 5 minutes.
Add tea, fruit syrup, juices and pineapple.
Let stand at least 30 minutes. Strain. Add cold water to make 1 1/2 gallons liquid. Add cherries and club soda.
Serve over ice in punch bowl. Serves 50.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add salt.
Remove meat.
In same skillet, cook onions and mushrooms; cover for 3 to 4 minutes.
Put to side. Blend flour and paprika in drippings.
Add Worcestershire sauce. Stir and cook until thick.
Return meat
and stir in sour cream. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: apple-stuffed squash
directions: Cut
squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Wash, core and dice apples.
Combine with syrup and margarine.
Fill squash with this mixture.	Brush with margarine.
Place inside 14-inch Dutch
oven
and
pour
in a 1/4 cup of boiling water. Bake 1 hour at medium heat.
Make
sure
water	level is maintained. Replenish water as necessary.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with extra crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Stir and set aside to cool. Combine cake mix, oil, lemon extract and beaten eggs.
Mix well on medium speed with mixer.
Now slowly add the Jell-O.
Pour into oiled and floured tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix 1 cup chopped pecans, flour and butter together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Let cream cheese soften and cream together with powdered sugar.
When blended, mix in 5 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled pecan mixture.
Mix pudding mix, milk and vanilla together. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Let chill and then spread on remaining 3 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top. Keep refrigerated.
Try coconut cream pudding instead of lemon. It's good also.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix and put in tiny muffin pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. These are so easy and so quick.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat sugar, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal (uncooked).
Shape into small mounds on waxed paper.

title: dieters soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender.
Eat twice a day to lose weight.

title: "the original" hillary clinton's chocolate chip cookies!
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
With electric mixer on high speed, beat shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually stir in flour mixture and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by well rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden.
Cool on baking sheet.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen. Each contains 68 calories, 1 gram protein, 4 grams fat, 5 mg cholesterol, 8 grams carbohydrates and 36 mg sodium.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and milk until creamy.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
Can be doubled and made in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make own graham cracker crust.

title: uncle scott's gumbo
directions: Heat olive oil in iron skillet and add flour to make dark brown roux.
Stir constantly.
Do not burn (takes 45 to 60 minutes).
Add chopped onion and bell pepper to roux for 5 to 10 minutes.
Boil water in a large pot and add roux to water.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.
Serve over rice, sprinkled lightly with file powder.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pineapple.
Layer cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix all over top of wet layer.
Cut up butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: peach custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cornstarch and melted butter together.
Put peaches in baking dish and pour mixture over top, mixing it together.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: fruit tray
directions: Wash and stem grapes.
Peel and cut up cantaloupe and mush melon.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Slice red and green apples.
Drain pineapple.
Make sure to sprinkle "Fruit Fresh" over apples or they will turn brown.
More fruit may be used that are in season. Fruit may be prepared the night before and stored in ZipLoc bags in the refrigerator.
Apples do best if they aren't sliced too far ahead of time.
Place on tray or in a bowl and serve with fruit dip.
Serves 40 people.

title: elnora's spanish chicken
directions: Layer the Doritos, chicken, onions, peppers and cheese. Repeat until meat is used up.
Cover with mushroom soup and chicken broth (mixed together).
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: summer salad
directions: Whisk together vinegar, oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Add cucumbers, onions and tomatoes; mix well. Add basil; stir. Add Feta and stir. Feta will break up into smaller pieces when you stir the salad. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a large skillet, heat olive oil. Add garlic, onion, zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Add broccoli and broth. Cover and steam 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is just tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes, parsley, lemon juice and seasonings.
Toss thoroughly.
Serve over spaghetti. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Makes 4 servings.

title: royal icing(cole-big recipe)
directions: Makes hard icing for decorations.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions over medium heat until beef is browned. Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand mixer).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with cheese of your choice and bake until cheese is melted.

title: salad "in the pink"
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve all juice.
Add juice to gelatin in a saucepan; stir in 1 cup of water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly to dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold or cut into squares.
Serve on salad greens. Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, oil and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, soda and salt.
In a third bowl, mix cocoa, food coloring and 1/2 cup of buttermilk.
Slowly add the cocoa mixture to the eggs, sugar and oil mixture.
To this, add the flour mixture alternately with other 1/2 cup of buttermilk.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 27 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool before frosting.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes, soup, onion and cheese in buttered dish.
Pour milk over top; cover with cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pan or use papers. Sift together the dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda); set aside.
Pour milk over oats. Add brown sugar, egg and oil; mix well.
Stir in sifted ingredients. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour batter into pan.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls of Cream Cheese Filling over batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: white jello
directions: Whisk 1/4 cup cold water and Knox gelatine until blended.
Add boiling water and mix until Knox is dissolved.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Mix well. Slowly fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, until set.
Can be poured into a mold.
Tastes like cheese cake!
Great with ham.

title: onion bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put on stove (turn stove on low heat) until warm and margarine melts.
With another bowl mix yeast, sugar and warm water.
After yeast dissolves, mix warm mixture with eggs. Fold in flour until sticky.
Leave in bowl and let rise for 1 hour. Take out and knead, then put in 2 loaf pans.
Let rise, then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush with margarine.

title: spicy applesauce muffins
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add margarine, sugar and applesauce. Sift together dry ingredients and add to yeast mixture.
Stir in raisins and ground pecans.
Stir only long enough to mix well. Cover and let rise 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add mayonnaise to taste.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In large skillet, cook onions with butter over low heat for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Add chopped mushrooms and cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add flour and cook, stirring for 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Turn heat to low and add half and half in a steady stream whisking while pouring.
Bring soup to a steady/gentle boil over moderate heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper.
Serves 4.
Tastes better made ahead and reheated.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Cook all ingredients in slow cooker until vegetables are tender.
Add no salt.

title: texas meatballs and rice(microwave)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until meatballs are set pink color, 4 to 6 minutes.
Rearrange meatballs after the cooking time; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Microwave at High until mixture is bubbly and onion is tender, 4 to 7 minutes.
Stir after half the cooking time.
Let stand until rice is tender, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine broth, parsley and butter in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.

title: dilled carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs, 1/3 cup butter and 3 tablespoons sugar until blended.
Pack mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press firmly to bottom and sides.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes, then allow to cool.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into two 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk and salt.
Add enough of the flour to make a very stiff dough.
Turn out on a floured board.
Roll dough very thin.
Let dough rest 20 minutes.
Roll dough up loosely; cut into 1/2-inch wide slices.
Unroll and cut into desired lengths.
Spread out noodles and let dry 2 hours.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour to measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift again.
Stir in milk.
Dough must be stiff enough to handle easily.
Roll dough on board; cut into small biscuits.
Lay in single layer.
Cover and boil for 20 minutes without raising lid.

title: honey baked chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of chicken.
Cut wings into two sections at joint, season with salt and pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients until well blended. Place chicken in baking dish, top with sauce and cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: heavenly delight cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening & sugar. Add nuts, flour & extracts. Form into small balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°. While hot roll in powdered sugar. Roll again in powdered sugar.

title: chicken on rice
directions: Blend soup with milk, reserving 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Stir together the remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 package onion soup mix.
Pour this into an ungreased baking dish. Place chicken on rice mixture.
Pour on reserved soup and sprinkle with remainder of onion soup mix.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pop cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed.
Let cake cool.
Punch holes in cake, then pour the Jell-O (prepared as directed) and soda over the cake.

title: lazy daz salad
directions: In a bowl, mix the crushed pineapple and pudding mixes.
Add a little over half of the Cool Whip and half the coconut.
Put mixture in a
square bowl.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of mixture.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Let refrigerate.

title: thanksgiving day wild rice stuffing
directions: Saute, in 1/2 cup of butter, then onions, mushrooms and celery; salt lightly.
In large bowl, combine bread, pecans and seasonings. Add sauteed vegetables.
Saute wild rice in remaining 1/2 cup butter and chicken broth; simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice to bread mixture.
Combine thoroughly.
Makes 12 cups.
Will stuff a 12 to 14 pound turkey, or cook separately for 40 minutes in a covered dish.

title: ken's lazy man's pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into dish.
Heat and sweeten fruit to taste.
Pour into batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and margarine and let set until soft.
Mix in flour.
Press out.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
(This is obviously not a low-fat recipe.
You may wish to get rid of the fat that rises to the top).
Serve warm with crackers.

title: pizza
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Spread crust evenly into 13-inch greased pizza pan.
Bake crust at temperature listed on can for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread sauce evenly over crust.
Top with cooked ground beef, onion, pepper and cheese. Continue baking 10 more minutes.
Top with pepperoni and bake an additional 2 minutes, if desired.

title: frilly dilly's
directions: Cut hot dogs into small pieces.
Mix with mustard and grape jelly.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: baked apple turnovers
directions: Cut pastry into 8 (4 1/2-inch) circles. Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons cooked apples on 1/2 of each circle. Moisten edges with water; fold dough over apple mixture, pressing edges to seal. Crimp edges with a fork. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over turnovers.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine together.
Roll into balls about the size of a marble.
Melt wax in double boiler (1 square) and add chocolate morsels.
Leave in heat and dip the balls of candy.
Place on wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beans with onion, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard.
Pile into casserole dish.
Stir in broken cooked bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbling well.

title: fried pork chops
directions: Wash chops.
In small bowl mix egg and water.
Put enough flour to coat chops in dinner plate.
Salt and pepper chops, then dip in egg and water.
Cover chips completely with flour.
Cook chops on medium heat until crust is browned.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread in a coffee can
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add pumpkin, water and oil; mix again.
Then add dry ingredients, then nuts and raisins; mix. For baking, use 4 one pound coffee cans.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Spoon into Bundt pan.
Shake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place boned chicken in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing over chicken mixture.
Melt butter in chicken broth and dribble over chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook hollowed out peppers in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: scarola insalata(italian salad)
directions: Pull greens apart into bite size pieces and pile in a large bowl.
Add onion to greens.
Add oil and mix thoroughly.
Add wine vinegar and mix again.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with spaghetti and Italian bread.

title: barbecued cole slaw
directions: Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Will keep refrigerated a week or more; lid must be kept on.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate several hours (overnight is best).

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in	large
baking
pan.
Spread brown sugar evenly in pan
and
arrange pineapple slices on sugar, filling in spaces with
pecans.
(You
can
add maraschino cherries in the pineapple centers.)
Mix
flour,
baking
powder
and salt together.	Beat egg yolks until light, adding sugar gradually. Add pineapple juice and
flour.
Fold	in
stiffly beaten egg whites.	Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn upside down on cake plate.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Roll out half and line 9-inch pie pan for pastry shell.
Combine strawberries with rhubarb.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into fruit thoroughly.
Turn into pastry shell.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Roll out remaining pastry for top crust.
Place over filling and cut slits for steam to escape.
Trim and flute edges.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.
Yields 7 servings.

title: braunsweiger ball
directions: Mix Braunsweiger and relish with a fork until blended.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate.
When firm "frost" with softened cream cheese.
Refrigerate for an hour or two until firm.

title: butternut squash soup with roasted red bell peppers
directions: Quarter squash and remove seeds.
Place in a large Pyrex or glass dish, cut side down, in 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 375° until tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove skin and set aside. Roast red pepper under broiler, turning often.
Remove skin.
Dice pepper and onion and saute in butter with herbs.
Puree squash and pepper mixture in blender.
May need to puree in several batches. Add small amount of broth, if too thick.
Return to large pan. Add broth to desired consistency.
Finish with small amount of half and half for added richness (optional).
Serve warm with a dollop of sour cream.

title: hot corn
directions: Cook in slow cooker on low.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter until fluffy; add peanut butter.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add oatmeal and baking soda and mix, then add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: shrimp in wine
directions: Combine flour, cheese and garlic powder in large bowl. Moisten shrimp with water and dredge in flour mixture.
Heat large skillet and then pour approximately 1/8-inch olive oil in pan. Brown shrimp lightly, but do not cook thoroughly.
Remove from pan.
(Add additional olive oil as necessary.)
Drain oil from pan, leaving flour and shrimp remnants.
Heat pan and deglaze with sherry and Marsala.
When wine mixture comes to a boil, simmer shrimp for approximately 20 seconds, or until cooked.
Do not overcook.
Garnish with chopped scallions.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the tomato sauce.
Shape into small balls and place in a frying pan.
Cover meatballs with tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Cover with a lid and simmer until done.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all in large bowl.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° until done in greased Bundt pan.

title: fish on the grill
directions: Split fish open lengthwise.
Put slice of onion, salt, seasoning salt, clove garlic, pepper and Parmesan cheese inside each fillet.
Put on grill for approximately 45 minutes or in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: creamy ham and chicken medley
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Remove from saucepan and set aside.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in whipping cream and next 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in mushrooms, chicken and ham.
Add enough of remaining milk for a thinner consistency.

title: apricot muffins
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in buttermilk, which has been mixed with soda.
Mix together the next 7 ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in raisins and apricots.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Bake in greased muffin tin at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt, butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add eggs. Add pecans. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Add water to egg whites and beat until frothy.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix.
Add pecans.
Spread mixture on two well-greased cookie pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring each 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green peppers, tomatoes, pickles and onions. Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add to cabbage mixture and mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Better if chilled for several hours before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together cream of mushroom soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish layer broccoli, chicken breast, soup mixture, bread crumbs and cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can serve as is or over noodles or rice.

title: alaska king crab casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and chicken stock with soup diluted in milk.
Stir and cook slowly until thickened.
Add milk to make a medium sauce.
Mix in herbs, mushrooms, seasonings and juice. Place crabmeat in large casserole.
Mix in lemon peel with fork. Pour sauce over this mixture and combine gently.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: thora's casserole
directions: Cook
noodles;	drain
and
set
aside.
Brown chuck in skillet
in
1 tablespoon butter.
Remove excess fat from pan; stir
in
tomato sauce.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream	and onion.
In a buttered 2 quart casserole spread half
the noodles.	Cover with cheese mixture, then cover with remaining
noodles.
Melt remaining butter; pour over noodles. Pour meat
and
sauce
mixture
over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: brown and serve pan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add shortening, sugar, salt, vinegar, egg and half of flour.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: ham rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook asparagus according to package directions and drain.
Wrap 2 ham slices around 2 or 3 asparagus stalks.
Place in an ungreased baking dish.

title: baked linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to directions and stir in the tomatoes, spaghetti sauce, onions and mushrooms.
Pour into a baking dish and top with shredded cheese.
(At this time you may refrigerate and put on the topping at baking time, if desired. Warm in microwave if it is refrigerated before pouring on the topping.)
Mix the milk and Bisquick and spread over linguine mixture with cheese.
Sprinkle Italian herbs, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, until topping is brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients but do not overbeat.
Add pecans, pour into pie crust.
Bake in a pre-heated 350 degree oven for 45-55 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients (except crackers and melted butter).
Pour in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top, then melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a microwavable dish.
Microwave for 2 minutes and stir.
Continue until smooth and creamy.
Serve warm. Best when served with sliced apples.
May use any fruit.

title: pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix in order and put in crusts.
Keep in icebox.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar and beat well.
Add half of milk and half of flour.
Mix, then add rest of milk and flour.
Add baking powder and melted oleo.
Add egg white last.
This can be used for pancakes.
Leftover batter can be frozen.

title: potato flake chicken
directions: Mix potato flakes, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder in large bowl.
Beat egg in a separate bowl and dip chicken breasts in egg. Then coat with potato flake mixture and place in baking dish. Top with melted butter and bake at 350° or until done.
Best if served with mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally and pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon and soda.
Grease and flour sheet pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: palm's summer pie
directions: Cook until thick. Pour into cooked crust. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Put layer of chips in bottom of oblong, glass baking dish. Cover with layer of cheese.
Mix chicken, soups, tomatoes and onion.
Pour over cheese and chips.
Top with another layer of chips and grated cheese.
Bake until bubbling and cheese is melted at 375°.

title: microwave rhubarb dessert
directions: Put rhubarb in 8 x 8-inch dish. Sprinkle sugar and dry jello over rhubarb.
Then dry cake mix.
Dribble melted butter on top. Cover with Saran Wrap and bake
15 minutes on High in microwave. Rotate dish midway.
Remove Saran Wrap when done baking.
Cover with waxed paper to cool.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Cook filling ingredients until thick.
Set aside.

title: chocolaholic sheet cake
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil the water, margarine and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix, then whisk in eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased jellyroll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir the first 6 items together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to melt sugar crystals on sides of pan.
Uncover, add peanuts and cook, stirring occasionally to hard crack stage (300°).
Stir in butter and soda.
Pour into a buttered 15 x 10-inch pan, spreading thinly.
Let brittle cool and break into pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook to softball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat by hand until mixture thickens.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Combine soup, enchilada sauce, milk and green chiles.
Heat until bubbly.
Dip tortillas in oil.
Do not fry.
Roll up meat, onion and some cheese in tortillas.
Put ends down.
Put in skillet.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Cook for 10 minutes.
You may put this in a casserole dish, also.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together dressing mix, cheese, parsley and garlic powder.
Dip chicken in melted butter, coating well. Then roll chicken in dressing mixture, packing heavily.
Place chicken in roasting pan lined with foil, taking care to not overlap chicken.
Drizzle any remaining butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with honey mustard.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take paper towel and dry moisture off each ham slice.
Let cream cheese set out to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread a very thin base on ham slice. Roll up ham slice long ways and place toothpicks in place.
Slice on each side of toothpick into bite size pieces. 1 ham slice makes around 10 roll-ups.

title: original hungarian goulash
directions: Brown veal and beef in oil.
Add tomatoes, onions, carrots and celery.
Simmer until vegetables are done to suit taste.
Add ketchup and more water if needed.
Lay potatoes on top and simmer until done.
Allow 1 hour.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Cube chicken, onion and bell pepper.
Saute in olive oil. Cook rice according to directions on package.
Let chicken cook on low.
After rice is cooked, dump in with chicken mixture.
Add soy sauce to chicken mixture; let cook for 5 minutes on low.

title: chicken wakiki beach
directions: Wash chicken; don't dry.
Salt, pepper and flour.
Toss chicken in flour.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Place pineapple juice in a 2 cup measuring cup.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid (you may use full strength juice, I do).
Put juice in a saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce and bouillon cube.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly. Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 30 minutes place pineapple rings on top of chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp nicholds
directions: Saute bacon.
Add oil and flour; brown for roux.
Add all vegetables and saute until tender.
Add raw rice and stir-fry about two minutes, stirring constantly, until rice changes color. Add raw shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink.
Add hot water, tomatoes and seasoning to taste.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour, cocoa, egg yolks and milk together. Microwave approximately 5 minutes. Stir and add butter and vanilla. Microwave 5 minutes more and stir. Microwave 2 minutes.

title: thick strawberry shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.
If using fresh berries, add 3 ice cubes to make a thicker shake.
Makes approximately one (12 ounce) serving; 79 calories.
Diabetic exchange, 1 fruit and 1/2 nonfat milk.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a little water.
Add all but last 2 other ingredients.
Take a package of Pepperidge Farm seasoned bread dressing and stick of margarine, melted and mix together. Put 1/2 of this on bottom of baking dish.
Add the zucchini mixture, then put the other half of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy golden frosting
directions: Melt butter with water.
Remove from heat.
Mix in egg yolks and lemon extract.
Mix in 3 cups powdered sugar.
If frosting is too stiff, add 1 teaspoon liquid slowly.
Makes enough for 2 layer cake.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice concentrate and pineapple juice; then add apple juice. Freeze in plastic jugs.
Before serving, thaw to a slush and add 3 litre bottle of Sprite or Ginger Ale. Serves 20 - 25.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Cook blackberries in water (covering berries).
Add 1 cup sugar while cooking.
Cook until berries are tender.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, egg, milk and flour; mix with spoon.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Get real hot, but do not boil. Let cool.
Pour in gallon jugs.
Store in pantry.
Does not need refrigeration.

title: crispy tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt together.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Roll real thin.
Bake in hot oven at 375° for 8 or 9 minutes.
Finely ground pecans may be added.
If handled correctly, this recipe will yield 112 small tea cakes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix 2 parts ketchup with 1 part Coke in any increment (i.e., 2 cups to 1 cup).
Add ketchup as needed for desired consistency. Great for spareribs.

title: german chocolate caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler.
Heat, stirring constantly until caramels are melted completely.
Remove from heat and set aside. Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Beat until mixture holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust and cover evenly with caramel mixture. Drop by teaspoon the remaining cake mix evenly over top.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.
Cool and then chill 30 minutes before cutting into small squares.

title: beef and tater squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and pat into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain off fat.
Combine 4 cups hot mashed potatoes with 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spread over meat and top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes, cut into squares and serve.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
When it becomes rather thick, whip. Mix thoroughly the cream cheese with pineapple.
Add celery and nuts, then add to whipped Jell-O.
Finally fold in Dream Whip which has been whipped until stiff.
Let set.

title: garlic pizza
directions: Stretch dough to fit pizza pan.
Make indentations with fingers in the dough.
Spread olive oil all over dough.
Sprinkle with chopped garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes.
Five minutes before pizza is done, sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to the oven and finish cooking.

title: sour cream veggie dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with cut up veggies.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: ham stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top off and seed 4 peppers; boil in salted water 2 minutes.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and add tomato juice to make moist enough to hold together.
Stuff peppers.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Place in baking dish close enough to touch.
Pour tomato juice in dish around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and drain.
In same skillet, add cream cheese to sausage.
Heat until melted.
Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Stuff mushrooms heaping full with sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide cake in half.
Crumble half sheet cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread half of pudding (made by directions on box) over cake.
Add half of other ingredients in order given.
Repeat for second layer.
Garnish with cherries or any way you wish. Refrigerate.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, flour, oil and eggs. Stir in chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then transfer to rack to finish cooling.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg in medium bowl with hand beater until fluffy.
Mix with next 7 ingredients until smooth, then cook and eat.

title: fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line 2 loaf pans with lightly greased parchment paper.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat 2 minutes.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour with fruit and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and spices.
Stir into oil mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pour batter over fruit mixture.
Blend well.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Dip tortillas in 1 cup warm chicken broth until wilted.
Lay 6 in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish, overlapping.
Boil onion, pepper and chili pepper in 1/2 cup chicken stock.
Add soup and tomatoes.
Place a layer of chicken meat on tortillas.
Pour soup mixture over it.
Repeat tortillas, chicken and soup layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars(makes 48)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine or butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk, then remaining 2 eggs, pumpkin, remaining 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice and salt. Mix well.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill; cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: perky dressing
directions: Add French dressing to sour cream; fold in lightly.
Makes 1/2 cup.
Serve with baked potatoes or other vegetable salads.

title: stir-fried chicken and cashews
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and sherry; set aside.
In a 12-inch skillet or wok, stir-fry cashews in hot oil over high heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until browned.
Lift out with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Add the chicken mixture to the skillet.
Stir-fry over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until just done.
Stir in hoisin sauce and cashews.
If desired, sprinkle with sliced green onion.
Serve at once with hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If recipe is too large, freeze half for later.

title: quick stir-fry
directions: Heat skillet to medium-high heat.
Add oil and when sizzling hot, add meat, vegetables, garlic and ginger and stir-fry until meat is done and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Blend cornstarch with chicken broth or with bouillon and water.
Stir into meat and vegetable mixture.
Add soy sauce and reduce heat.
Cook for 5 more minutes.

title: mini crepes with asparagus
directions: Make 3 small crepes from each large one, using round cookie cutter.
Cook asparagus spears until crisp-tender.
Cut off tips of spears so that each will be about 1/2-inch longer than the diameter of each little crepe.
Spread each crepe with cheese; place asparagus tip in center and roll up.
Serve at room temperature or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna.
Cook ground beef and turkey; drain.
Stir in all ingredients except cheeses and olives.
Layer lasagna noodles and meat mixture, then cheeses.
Top with olives.
Bake, covered with foil, 25 minutes at 375°, then uncovered for 20 minutes more. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar together real well until creamy.
Add Choco Bake, 1 egg and vanilla; beat 5 minutes.
Add 1 egg; beat another 5 minutes.
Double usually.
Put in crust and cool for 1 to 2 hours.

title: beef casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, ketchup, Cheddar cheese, green pepper, onion, salt and 1/2 can fried onions.
Add the ground beef (cooked) and the cooked macaroni to the soup mixture; mix.
Cover, bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover, sprinkle with remaining onions and return to oven and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pineapple cherry crisp
directions: Empty cherries and crushed pineapple into an oblong pan. Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over (drizzle) entire pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Saut chicken (or shrimp) until done.
Remove form pan and saut celery and onion.
Add bean sprouts, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and drained mushrooms (if desired).
When celery and onions are half-tender, add liquid from vegetables to cornstarch. Blend and pour in pan.
Return chicken (or shrimp) to pan and cook to desired consistency (this doesn't take long).
Serve with rice and chow mein noodles, if desired.
Also, soy sauce is good.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: hot dill sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with an electric mixer.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: picnic baked ham
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add onion.
Mix with beans and other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chopped chicken, onions, olives, peppers and 1/2 cup cheese.
Set aside.
Cook and stir garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in sauce, water and chili powder.
Heat through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons filling on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in rectangular baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Spoon remaining chicken filling over tortillas.
Pour sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake until hot, 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sin pie
directions: Mix well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven at 450°.
Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves; stir in pumpkin.
Add vanilla, evaporated milk and egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until a knife inserted in filling comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
Approximate calories per serving:

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Mix
cream
cheese, sugar and flour.
Add vanilla, eggs and heavy
cream.
Mix	well.
Preheat	oven
to
Pour filling into a 9-inch spring-form pan that has been lined with a
cookie crumb
crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250°. Continue baking for 1 hour longer.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon (remove any bones). Add remaining ingredients. Mix well with a fork. Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: tollerini(ground beef casserole)
directions: Fry meat, onions and peppers until brown.
Add tomato soup, paste, creamed corn and ripe olives to beef mixture.
Mix well. Fold in cooked noodles and put in a casserole dish.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: gold 'n nut crunch
directions: Mix nuts and margarine.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Bake at 300° on cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Stir in cereal.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: texas beef bake
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Drain; add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes in covered casserole dish. Top with cheese and return to oven for 3 minutes.
Serves 4. Double ingredients for 8.

title: feather cakes(pancakes)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with a fork.
In a separate bowl, beat egg with a fork, then blend in oil.
Mix well and finally add milk.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture and mix well, beating out any large lumps.
Bake on a hot griddle or frying pan by pouring 1/4 cup of batter onto lightly greased hot pan.
Turn when bubbles form on top and edges are dry.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, oatmeal, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel and boil potato.
When done, mash with a fork.
Add a little salt and box of 10x sugar (1 pound).
This makes a stiff dough.
Roll out on well floured surface to 1/4-inch thick. Spread peanut butter all over top.
Roll up like a jelly roll (make 2).
Put this in the refrigerator.
Chill.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Chill all ingredients together thoroughly except ginger ale. Just before serving, add ginger ale that has been chilled.
Serves 50.

title: moist orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello together. Combine eggs, water and salad oil. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease pan (10 x 14-inch or larger).
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix pecans and coconut and spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spoon over cake batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage and chili strata
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat and drain well.
Add chilies and mix.
Cube bread.
Put half of bread in bottom of an oiled lasagna pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of meat and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.

title: incredible meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 3/4-inch meatballs. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: ari's pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell. Mix well and turn into shell. Bake at 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake another 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Cool for several hours or overnight in the refrigerator. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lobscow
directions: Place layer of meat, onions, potatoes and tomatoes (or soup) in baking pan or dish.
Season; dot with butter.
Repeat layers of ingredients until used.
Pour water over all and bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: boot's pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, blend pumpkin, butter and spices.
Add sugars and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake for 45 minutes. Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Place apples in buttered 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Jell-O over apples.
Combine flour and sugar in small bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orzo(great for parties)
directions: Cook orzo and drain.
Mix in onion soup packets with mushrooms.
Pour onion mixture and mix well.
Serve warm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. For each cup, use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Combine soy sauce and dressing.
Add pork chops; cover and marinate for several hours.
(May vary amounts of soy and dressing, just use equal amounts.)
Cook on grill.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn in large dishpan that has been buttered on bottom.
Boil sugar, syrup, salt and water until small amount forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Pour slowly over popped corn, stirring corn with long handled spoon to coat corn evenly.
Butter your hands and shape into size balls desired.
Let balls stand until brittle.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Whip 10 minutes, then 5 minutes on slow.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in heated juice of pear and water.
Cool to egg white consistency.
Soften cream cheese and add to cream.
Add to whipped Jell-O.
Mash the pears and add to the Jell-O and cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: apple delight
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Very good warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add the sausage.
Let simmer half hour.
Sauce can be frozen and reused.
Makes good appetizers.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix in baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over soup mix.
Spread soups over the rice and add water.
Place chicken over mixture and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: linda's icebox surprise
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour, butter and nuts in a bowl.
Mix well (mixture will be crumbly).
Put mixture in the bottom of rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If you do not wish to bake or make this crust, you may use graham cracker pie crust already made up.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch and 7-Up (add 1/2 of 7-Up at a time).
Add 1/2 sherbet; stir slowly or mixture will become very foamy.
Add strawberries and the remainder of 7-Up and sherbet.
Makes 25 to 30 (6 ounce) servings.
Use 1 (8 pound) bag of ice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain raisins, reserving the liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken jack
directions: Pound chicken and roll around cheese sticks.
Place in baking pan.
Beat egg, brush each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and parsley and dressing.
Combine soups, wine and mushrooms, stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pam's fruit salad
directions: Combine yogurt, juice and sugar.
Pour over fruit. Refrigerate.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix fried hamburger, 1/2 water, 1/2 salsa and taco seasoning. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put crescent rolls in an 8-inch baking dish as the crust.
Come up the sides of the pan halfway; pinch seams together.
Layer 1 cup crushed tortillas, meat mixture, sour cream, cheese and 1/2 cup of tortilla chips.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until crescent rolls are done and the cheese is melted. Serve with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Saut celery, bell pepper and onion in sausage drippings. Stir sausage and vegetables together. Add soups, rice and water. Place in casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes, covered. Remove from oven and cover with cheese (2 cups) and almond slivers. Return to oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chanukah symbol cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, beat butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, beating until blended.
Divide dough into 2 equal portions.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, 1 hour or longer.
Prior to baking, allow dough to stand at room temperature until soft enough to roll.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix everything except flour and oatmeal.
Gradually add flour and last add oatmeal. Spoon 1 tablespoon size onto baking sheet. Bake until edges lightly brown, about 7 to 8 minutes.
May omit pecan pieces, if desired.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; put in a casserole dish.
Press out like a pie crust.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Add cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer.
Pour into rice.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine, add grated cheese, blend well. Add flour, salt and pepper. Dough should be a little crumbly, not too smooth. Use cookie press and place dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Cut each strip into 3 - 4 inch pieces before cooking. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 - 14 minutes.

title: audrey's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a skillet.
Drain.
Put remaining ingredients and beef mixture in a large pot and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: duke's mixture
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Divide evenly into 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.

title: cajun mushrooms
directions: Wash and trim mushrooms. Place some butter in frying pan and add enough mushrooms to cover bottom. Use medium heat; sprinkle with garlic powder to coat. Add 3 tablespoons teriyaki sauce and a few shakes of Tabasco sauce. Add splash of wine if desired. Cook for about 5 to 10 minutes. Do not overcook. When cooked, transfer to a crock-pot, saving the liquid in another pot. Continue making batches until complete. Bring reserved liquid to boil and slowly add flour to make gravy. Cook until pastry taste is gone. Pour over mushrooms in crock-pot; heat on low until ready to serve, adding more Tabasco sauce if spicier flavor is desired.

title: cinnamon cream apple crumb pie
directions: Roll out pastry to fit into a 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan.
Flute edges.
In large bowl combine apples, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg.
Spoon mixture in pastry shell. Combine 3/4 cup flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes, until filling is bubbly and top is golden.
Stir cinnamon into cream.
With a wooden pick or skewer poke tiny holes in crumb top as soon as the pie is removed from oven.
Very slowly pour cream over the top so that it is absorbed.
Let stand until cool or serve hot with ice cream.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, milk and egg.
Shape into 20 meatballs.
Brown well in shortening.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle meatballs with flour; stir gently to coat. Combine tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce and salt.
Pour over meatballs. Simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until desired consistency. Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles, if desired.

title: zucchini parmigiana
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Cut each half crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Should have about 6 cups.
Set aside.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie crust for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: haluski with sauerkraut
directions: On dough board, measure flour.
Make a well in the center. Add egg and salt.
Knead well until dough is smooth.
Let stand a few minutes, then roll out thinly and cut into little squares. Cook in boiling water about 10 minutes.
Drain and add to prepared sauerkraut.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with syrup in the pistachio pudding mix. Add Cool Whip. Add marshmallows and walnuts. Mix lightly. Refrigerate.

title: no name muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Place in muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock pot on low until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer cake, berries and glaze.
Repeat until all is used.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt; then add to mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Mix everything together.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix sausage and bisquik thoroughly.
Add cheese. Mix well. Roll out on floured surface.
Roll up like jelly roll, wrap in saran wrap, and refrigerate until firm.
Slice and bake in 350 degree oven until brown.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water.
Remove; drain.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Stuff peppers.
Place upright in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Leftover peppers freeze well.)

title: pizza planks(kids)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place bread on a cutting board. Carefully split bread in half lengthwise.
Remove some of the soft bread to make a slightly hollow loaf.
Place each half on the baking sheet, cut sides up.
Spoon spaghetti sauce evenly over both halves.
Arrange pepperoni, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese evenly on the tops.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Use your imagination when making Pizza Planks.
Add your favorite toppings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook pie shell a little before filling with mixture.
Mix all ingredients together and turn into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 30 or 35 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Stir in vanilla. Add eggs. Stir in flour and salt. Chill 2 hours. Roll out 1/4 of dough at a time, rolling to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut into desired shapes and lift to baking sheet with spatula. Place cookies 1 inch apart. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or to light brown. Remove from cookie sheet. Cool, frost and decorate.

title: veggie taco or pocket
directions: Zap bread in microwave for 1/2 minute.
It makes taco shells or pita bread easier to work with.
Put tahini on first, then add other ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Use one can of shrimp plus all other ingredients and process in food processor until well blended.
Add 2nd can of shrimp and refrigerate until serving.
Elegant and easy.

title: skillet paella
directions: In a frying pan or electric fry pan saute onion, red and green peppers and garlic in oil.
Add broth, vinegar and seasonings. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts and rice; mix thoroughly.
Place seafood on top.
Cover and simmer until heated thoroughly and seafood is cooked.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salad supreme
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish, coated with vegetable spray.
Chill until partially set.
Top with pineapple and first 1/2 cup of pecans.
Combine Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread mixture over pineapple layer and chill.

title: chicken crunch with lemon parsley sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°. In medium bowl, mix 1/3 c. soup and 1/4 c. milk. Lightly coat chicken with flour. Dip into soup mixture. Coat with stuffing. Place chicken on baking sheet. Drizzle with the melted oleo. Bake 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. In small saucepan mix remaining soup, remaining milk, lemon juice and parsley. Over medium heat, heat through. Serve with chicken. Serves 4.

title: ground beef barbecue
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Add salt and pepper; simmer 1/2 hour.
Place mixture in a greased oblong baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over beef mixture and mix well in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine all ingredients (pastry blender is helpful). Make into balls and mash with fork. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet 10-12 minutes at 400 degrees. Makes 6 dozen.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes; remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Have instant oatmeal and coconut mixed to stir in mixture.
Drop from tablespoon on greased cookie sheet. Raisins or nuts may replace coconut.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Cook noodles according to package. Combine all ingredients except cheese. Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: boston cream pie
