directions: Prepare pudding mix as package directs using milk and spread between cake layers.
In small saucepan, over low heat, blend chocolate and butter until melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sugar and vanilla.
Gradually stir in enough water until reaching a glaze consistency, drizzle over the cake.

title: sausage chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish and set aside.
Cook sausage, onion, carrot and celery in a large skillet until sausage is brown.
Drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Stir chicken into sausage.
Mix and set aside.

title: frosty vegetable salad
directions: Mix the sour cream, Miracle Whip, garlic salt, sugar and dill weed together first.
Add cut up vegetables.
Chill before serving.

title: japanese pie
directions: Cream
margarine
and sugar;
add eggs, mixing well and add other
ingredients.
Bake
at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set in center.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Mix all except cheese together in a bowl and spread in a baking dish.
Place slices of cheese on top.
Bake in oven until light brown at 375° for 30 minutes in a 7 x 11-inch or 9-inch square dish.

title: almond broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cut up and cook the chicken breast and lightly cook the broccoli.
Place broccoli on bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Spread chicken over broccoli.
Mix cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Top casserole with the slivered almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fancy french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over bread that has been placed in a greased baking dish.
Let bread sit for a scant minute and turn over.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, press in raw hamburger, salt and pepper.
Slice and layer potatoes.
Slice and layer onion and pour cream of chicken soup on top.
(Do not add water).
Cook, covered, approximately 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done at 350°.

title: christina's guacamole
directions: Scoop out middle of avocados and smash with a fork or potato masher.
Cut up tomato and onion; combine with avocados.
Squeeze lemon or lime in the mixture.
Chop garlic and add to the mixture. If you are using garlic powder, sprinkle a desirable amount.
Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead very well.
Shape into 1 large or 2 medium size balls.
Sprinkle heavy with chili powder. Then roll balls in chopped pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool layers.

title: cooked cream cheese dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese in baking dish. Season with garlic salt. Next, spread chili, then chopped onion. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake until cheese is well melted.

title: strawberry dressing
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients.
Fold in yogurt.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Serve over honeydew wedges or strawberries.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease. Add all ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer 1 hour. Add 2 sliced carrots and cook 10 minutes.
Add 1 large potato, cubed, and cook 20 minutes more.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, seasoning mix, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
We like this over Fritos and with hot dogs the next day for lunch.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy cheesy coffee cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Set aside. Pat 1 tube of crescent roll onto cookie sheet.
Spread on cheese mixture.
Top with remaining tube.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Spread on top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° for 20 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Make Ahead:
This luscious cheesecake may be made 1 day ahead through step 3. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and refrigerate. Add topping and decorate with pecans before serving.

title: hamburg-pea soup
directions: Put 2-inches of water in pan.
Break up hamburg.
Put into water.
Chop onion very fine.
Dice potatoes.
When hamburg is done, add juice off peas.
Add potatoes and onion.
When done, add peas.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add egg, milk and peanut butter; stir just until combined.
Pour into a greased 8x4x2 in. loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack. Serve with jelly if desired.

title: no-bake mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of each of 12 paper or foil-lined muffin cups with spoon or bottom of glass.
Beat milk and filling mix until blended.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumb mixture in muffin cups.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with fruit, nuts or chocolate.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: vinaigrette salad
directions: Arrange romaine, Feta cheese, onions and olives on 4 salad plates. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar with tight-fitting lid and shake well. Just before serving, pour vinaigrette over salad.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add chopped dates; cook slowly until they are dissolved.
Remove from stove; beat until thick and creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla; turn mixture at once onto a cloth which has been wrung out of cold water.
Roll in cloth.
When cool, unroll and slice into 3/4-inch pieces.

title: chicken in apple-mustard sauce
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of waxed paper. With a heavy knife, pound chicken breasts to flatten to about 1/2-inch thick.
Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and saute about 3 minutes on each side until brown. Add apple juice, onion, garlic and thyme.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; keep warm. Heat liquid to boiling; add mustard.
Stir until well blended. Add apple slices.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: light bread biscuits
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water and yeast and set aside. Mix everything but yeast well. Then add yeast. Mix again. Let mixture set for about 5 minutes. Add mixture to 1-gallon crock of flour, forming hole in center of bowl (in flour). Pour mixture in hole. Mix well, adding flour gradually. Put on a floured paper. Knead for about 5 minutes, adding a little flour as you knead. Put in pot with lid. Let raise 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Then punch down. Knead a few times, then separate (in halves). Then separate each half into 2 more sections of dough. (Should have 4 balls of dough.)

Then squeeze each ball into 3 more balls, making 12 round biscuits. Grease pan. Turn tops over in butter or grease in pan, then turn back over in pan (so tops will brown pretty). Let raise to double their size. Bake until golden brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bhugia(from india)
directions: Boil peas and potatoes separately.
When the potatoes are thoroughly done, drain and let them cool enough to handle.
Drain the peas.
Heat oil in a frying pan.
Slice the potatoes.
Saute the potatoes and peas together.
Season with salt and sprinkle with chopped green peppers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir in gradually and add bananas. Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Bake on a greased griddle.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown onion in bacon.
Add flour and blend well.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Cover and cook until done.
Add milk and chopped parsley.
Butter may also be added if desired.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: special pork chops
directions: On each pork chop, place 1 slice of onion, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and ketchup.
In covered casserole, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and corn syrup over low heat until smooth.
Add vanilla, powdered sugar and Krispies.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Store in fridge.

title: mint ice cream brownies
directions: Bake brownies in 12 x 15-inch shallow pan.
(I use a cookie sheet with sides.)
Don't overbake.
Cut in half.
Slice slightly softened ice cream lengthwise and lay on top one half of brownie, filling into all edges.
Place other half of brownie on top.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and then freeze.
If storing very long, wrap in foil.
Slightly thaw and cut to serve.

title: heavenly banana delight
directions: In bowl, mix pudding, condensed milk and milk for 2 minutes. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Whip cream, then add cream and sour cream to chilled pudding mixture.
In large dish or bowl, place a layer of vanilla wafers, layer of bananas and 1/2 pudding mix. Stream chocolate syrup over.
Repeat layers again.
Stream chocolate syrup over second layer.
Garnish top with nuts and/or cherries (optional).

title: fried drop cakes
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add milk, dry ingredients (mixed and sifted) and melted butter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot deep fat (370°).
Fry until light brown and cooked through.
(This can be determined by breaking one apart.)
Remove with a skimmer and drain on brown paper when done.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in blender.
If too thick, thin with vinegar.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream together; add egg yolk. Mix and add flour and mix well.
Spread on a buttered cookie sheet with hands and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
(Dough will be stiff.)
While this is baking, melt 1 large bar Hershey milk chocolate bar and about 6 ounces chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Spread on top of bars the minute you take them out of the oven and sprinkle with ground walnuts.
Cut in squares while warm and leave on cookie sheet several hours until chocolate hardens.

title: glazed apple bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add milk, apples and nuts to creamed mixture.
Mix flour, cinnamon and baking powder and stir only until mixture is well dampened.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan; turn out on wax paper and spread with glaze.

title: cheese and ham ball
directions: Chop 4 to 6 slices of ham.
Add cheese, onions and Accent. Mix together with hands.
Form into a ball and cover with 2 to 3 whole slices of ham. Serve with Club crackers.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serve. Even good for dessert.
Excellent with turkey, chicken and ham dishes.

title: cheese pasta dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water and spaghetti sauce mix; cook 30 minutes.
Boil macaroni and drain. Mix all together with sour cream.
Layer mixture with cheese.
Heat in oven until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco sauce and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Crumble 1/2 taco shells in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Layer 1/2 hamburger mixture over shells.
Cover with 1/2 cheese.
Layer rest of crumbled shells, then hamburger and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in long baking dish and completely cover with bacon strips.
Bake in 425° oven until bacon is brown and beans are slightly thick.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, oats, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, except candied cherries; stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Lightly press a cherry half into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets 10 minutes before transferring to cooling racks.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla with an electric blender.
Mix on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple right-side-up cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan. Melt butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of pan; drizzle butter over.
Cut pineapple rings in half and place 6 on top of brown sugar, forming a ring.
Cut remaining pieces in 3 pieces and place in between halves.
Place cherries in center of each half.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice zucchini in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix well.
Add 1 small jar Miracle Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, taco sauce, chilies and milk in a bowl.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper together.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut 1 package tortillas into 8ths.
Layer 1/2 tortillas into bottom of casserole dish. Then spread meat, sauce and shredded Cheddar cheese; repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chicken broth, carrots, chicken, sherry, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Freeze, if desired, in 8-cup freezer container.

title: russian tea
directions: Heat water, cloves and sugar to a boil.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes. Pour in rest of ingredients and let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Strain and store in refrigerator.
Serve hot.

title: spinach pudding
directions: Mix spinach, cottage cheese, salt, Parmesan and eggs until well blended.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Let sit a little after coming out of oven to meld juices.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: frijoles colorados - red beans
directions: Soak beans overnight covered in water.
Or use quick softening method:
bring beans to boil, boil for 5 minutes, cover and turn off heat.
Let beans sit for 1 hour and then begin recipe.
Make sure beans are covered by 2 fingers of water.
Cook beans on simmer with meat until tender.
In small frying pan, saute onion, green pepper and garlic in the olive oil with bay leaf.
Be careful not to burn garlic.
Add can of tomato sauce and the remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix well and add to beans.
Continue to cook beans until seasoning is well absorbed and beans are soft.
If using chorizo, add whole to sauce before adding to beans.

title: orange cooler
directions: In large punch bowl, mix together orange juice, ginger ale and crushed ice and half the orange slices.
Garnish with remaining oranges.
Serve cold.

title: confetti cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into 3 balls.
If desired, roll balls in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large pot, stir together 2 cups water, potatoes, celery, carrots, onion and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, simmer covered until all vegtables are tender and not overcooked (about 10 minutes)
Do not drain.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla; slowly add hot milk.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bate at 475° for 5 minutes and then at 425° for 10 minutes or until tester inserted in center of custard comes out clean.
Very, very good!
This bakes in 15 minutes and the crust isn't soaked.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: You will also need water soaked toothpicks.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken in butter or margarine; remove from pan and place in casserole dish.
To skillet, add onion and garlic; cook about 5 minutes.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir into onion mixture; gradually add chicken broth and bouillon cubes crumbled.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and add Sauterne.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in pan.
Place rice in bottom of oven dish or electric frypan.
Arrange chops and brown crumbs onto each pile of rice.
Arrange slice of thick tomato, thick onion ring and pepper ring on each chop (2 tablespoons of rice for each chop).
Pour your liquid on after you have arranged all in baking dish, then the butter.
Cook until rice and chops are done.

title: creamy vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to pkg. directions; drain and place in a large bowl.
Stir in soup and cream cheese.
Transfer to a greased 1 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: 9-day slaw
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil (do not include cabbage, pepper or onion).
Pour over vegetables.
Stir well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add tomatoes and blend with flour until smooth; add seasonings.
Boil 5 minutes while stirring.
Add hot milk; simmer a few minutes. Serves 4.
Will not curdle if directions are followed.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat in 9x13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Spread coconut evenly over top. Pour Eagle Brand milk over the coconut. Bake for 15 minutes. Add chocolate chips evenly over top and return to oven for 10-15 minutes. Cut into bars when cool.

title: baked fish(psari plaki sto fourno)
directions: Clean and wash fish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Squeeze the juice of the lemon over it.
Let stand 1 hour.
Clean the onions and slice thin; rinse with cold water.

title: deluxe ham and potato salad
directions: In a 1 quart saucepan, place eggs and enough water to come 1-inch above tops of eggs.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Remove saucepan from heat.
Cover tightly and let eggs stand in hot water for 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: potluck apple cake
directions: Combine apples, oil, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Add baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tropical fruit delight
directions: Serve dishes of fruit with dollop of yogurt and sprinkle of brown sugar.

title: sunrise breakfast casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sausage and 2/3 of cheese in buttered 9 x 13 dish. Pour egg/soup mixture over mixture, then top with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: graham date bars
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil; cook until thickened, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and dates.
Place whole crackers in a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan. Pour the first mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers on top.
Make glaze.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In a large (glass or metal) 13 x 9-inch pan, break the angel food cake into small pieces.
In a large mixing bowl, blend both boxes of vanilla pudding with the milk.
Then thoroughly mix the ice cream with it.
(Do not use thawed ice cream; it can be slightly softened.)
Pour evenly over cake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into shell and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: mandarin pineapple-orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Fold in softened sherbet and Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: garbage can dinner
directions: Purchase a new garbage can and wash out with bleach and water mixture.
Pull husks down and remove the silk from corn.
Wrap each husk around corn and stand on end in garbage can.
Scrub potatoes and carrots and put on top of corn.
Next, add onions, cabbage and sausage.
Pour 2 cans of beer and 1 can of water over top.
Secure garbage can lid.
Build a charcoal fire and place can on coals.
Do not remove lid.
After you notice steam coming out from under lid, continue to cook 2 hours.

title: doggie treats
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll out.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water; let set while mixing other ingredients.
Sift flour; add sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Add yeast and buttermilk; blend.
You can roll out immediately or place in refrigerator and use as needed.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix well cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Reserve 2/3 cup of mixture.
Spread remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Pour 1 1/2 cups butter, 3 eggs, chopped pecans, vanilla and dark brown sugar on top of crust and bake about 1 hour at 325°.
(You may want to check it after 45 minutes.)

title: flourless cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Flatten slightly with tines of fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on a nonstick or greased cookie sheet.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
To milk, shortening and 1 1/2 cups cold water, add gradually 10 to 12 cups flour. After mixing about 3 cups flour to water mixture, add yeast mixture.
Continue adding flour, until easy to knead and doesn't stick to board, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead until indentations spring back.
Grease top.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Rise in a warm place.
If oven is cool, set a pan of boiling water in bottom of oven.
Punch down and shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes. Remove from pans immediately.
Butter tops, if desired, while warm.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: chow chow
directions: Boil together vinegar, sugar, celery salt, mustard seed and turmeric.
Pour in cabbage, pepper and onions.
Bring to boil; can.

title: sinful strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix in bananas, nuts, strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half mixture into serving dish; chill.
When firm, spread sour cream onto salad and pour on the other half of mixture.
Cover, chill and serve.

title: mom's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and Wesson oil until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg, sugar and oil.
Then add pineapple, carrots, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour or longer at 320° until toothpick inserted in center of layer comes out clean.
Use two lined and floured 9-inch pans or tube pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pizza sauce and cheese. Combine milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Beat until smooth (batter will be thin).
Pour over casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well.
Add egg yolks and milk, mixing well after each.
Add butter and flavoring.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and spread over chocolate.
Bake until brown.
Let cool and eat it up!!

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Preheat the broiler. Cut the chicken into small cubes and prepare with the fajita seasoning mix. Broil 5 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink on the inside. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Heat oil in a large sauce pan over medium heat. Mix in the seasoned chicken, onion & pepper. Slowly cook and stir for 10 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender. Layer 1/2 of each tortilla with chicken mixture, cheese, and desired amount of bacon bits. Top with cheese. Fold the tortillas. Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese has melted.

title: chicken and stove top
directions: Combine all.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: cranberry salad-dessert
directions: Wash cranberries thoroughly and run through a food processor or blender to chop.
Add all ingredients together, whipped cream last.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in a greased 2 qt. baking dish until set.

title: german pound cake
directions: All ingredients must be at room temperature.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Sift 2 sugars together; add to butter.
Add unbeaten egg yolks; beat until smooth.
Mix in extracts; add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Grease Bundt pan, then pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Turn cake onto dish; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: nacho casserole(recipe of the month for april)
directions: Place 2 cups chips on bottom of 9-inch round microcook type shallow container.
Combine beef, salsa, tomato sauce and 2/3 cup cheese; pour over chips.
Cover with wax paper; cook on High for 9 minutes, turning 3 times.
Uncover; top with remaining chips and cheese.
Cook for 1 minute.
Garnish with avocado, tomato and olives.
Serves 4.

title: honeymoon cake
directions: Cook cake as directed. Mix sugar and pineapple together when cake comes out of the oven. While hot, punch holes in top and pour sugar and pineapple mixture over cake.

Mix instant pudding as directed and pour over cake. Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding. Sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped pecans over coconut. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box. Bake in 2 round pans. Cool. Mix sour cream and sugar, then add 1/2 can of coconut. Split each layer in half (making 4 layers). Put 1/4 of mixture with Cool Whip. Frost top and sides. Sprinkle with coconut on top. Refrigerate.

title: lemonade luxury
directions: Mix together lemonade,
Cool
Whip
and condensed milk. Pour into crust.
Cover
with
graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: chasen's chili(serves 4 quarts)
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover by 2 inches. Next day, pour beans and liquid into a large kettle; cover and simmer until tender, 1 to 2 hours.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: chad's chops
directions: Choose a casserole dish large enough to hold the chops in 1 layer.
Melt butter in pan.
Arrange chops.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Add cooked rice.
Mix catsup and Worcestershire with hot water and pour over rice and chops.
Sprinkle salt and pepper. Cover and bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup more water if it becomes too dry.
Serves 6.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Put into a bowl and add cream cheese, Ricotta cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, mix together soup, milk, wine, shrimp, crab meat, scallops and Parmesan cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Drain. Let cool. Then add vegetables and the Salad Supreme dressing, seeds and hot sauce. Pour the Italian dressing in last. Add at intervals until you get the moistness you want. Chill.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat cake mix, oil and egg on medium speed until crumbly (or by hand).
Add nuts. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mix and press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes.
After 20 minutes, before it's finished, take out and put cheese and paprika on top.
Finish cooking for 10 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and chip cheese, pimento and celery into pieces. Add salad dressing, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix gently and refrigerate for 1 hour or more.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Press into bottom and up sides of ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with oleo.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine ham, cheese and green pepper; spoon over crust.
In small bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Allow to stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: garfish balls
directions: Mix everything together and form into balls; roll in flour. Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Remove excess grease and make a brown roux with 1 cup flour to 1 cup oil.
Add chopped onion and stir about 1 or 2 minutes.
Add 1 to 2 cups water; place garfish balls in gravy.
Cover and cook slowly for about an hour. Season to taste. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese and gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, stirring until combined.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: southern cake
directions: Mix together and beat according to directions on box of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bitsy's corn bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Break egg into mixture. Combine all ingredients.
Oil pans and heat.
Bake at 350° to 400° until browned.

title: salmon noodle casserole
directions: Drain salmon; break into large chunks.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour and dry mustard.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Stir in vegetables, cooked noodles and 1 cup cheese. Gently fold in salmon.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll biscuits in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Stick in greased tube pan.
Combine oleo and brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Nuts may be added to the bottom or top, if desired.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Wash roast.
Season roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Place in crock-pot with 1/2 cup water.
Place sliced onion on top and cook overnight on low setting.

title: light and high lemon pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, lemonade and milk.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Garnish with candied lemon, if desired.

title: orange butter cake and filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetics pie
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sprinkle in dry jello and stir. Add cornstarch, pineapple, and fruit cocktail. Gently fold in cool whip. Fold into two pie shells, set in refrigerator.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, eggs, water, and vanilla until creamy.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by rounded tsp. onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 - 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cranberries and sugar and set aside 1 hour.
Mix the boiling water with cherry and lemon Jell-O.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate to congeal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together; pour in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
You may add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese the last minutes of baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: round steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well, pour over steak. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours or longer.
Grill or boil to desired doneness.
To serve, cut in strips against the grain.
Yields 8 portions.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart dish.
Crush corn flakes. Stir in 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs together well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately to margarine mixture.
Add nuts and lemon rind.
Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured pan.
When done, poke top with a toothpick.
Add lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar and pour over top.

title: venison barbecue
directions: Cook roast until tender; drain juice.
Tear roast apart with fork.
Add barbecue sauce.
Place in boiler on stove and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve as sandwich or with meal.

title: company sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt and mix well.
Add milk and butter and heat in double boiler.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten. Cook until thickened.
Add coconut and pour into cooked pie shell; brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and sugar or flour large jelly roll pan.
While cookies are still warm, frost with the following mix:

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil to 375°.
Mix egg and water until well mixed.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring to make a smooth batter.
Dip pieces of chicken in batter; fry in hot oil until golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with favorite sauce.

title: raspberry jam bars
directions: Stir together 1 3/4 cups flour and nuts.
In a larger bowl, beat butter until soft.
Add powdered sugar and beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture and beat until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of crumbs in bottom of ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread jam over base of crumbs.
Stir the 1 tablespoon flour into remaining crumb mix and sprinkle over jam.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are golden.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24. Enjoy!

title: spinach salad
directions: Salad can be assembled ahead and chilled to keep crisp.
Then add dressing and seeds just before serving.

title: funnel cake
directions: In a
12-inch
skillet	over
medium
heat,
heat about 3/4-inch oil to 325°.
In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix flour
and	next
5 ingredients.
Holding a narrow-spouted funnel, close
spout
with finger;
pour about 1/2 cup batter into funnel.
Remove finger to let batter run out in a stream while making
a 6-inch (diameter) spiral.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden
brown,
turning
once.
Drain
on paper towels. Sprinkle or sift with confectioners sugar.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables in large bowl.
Sprinkle on dry dressing. Spread with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight covered tightly. Just before serving, mix well.

title: dolly sods cake
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and sugar and let stand. Beat eggs slightly. Beat in oil and brandy. Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir flour mixture into liquid alternately with apple/cranberry/sugar mixture. Stir in black walnuts. Put batter (it will be stiff) into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Let stand until cool. Turn out on rack to complete cooling.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and roll into marble size meatballs.
Brown in margarine and garlic salt, not too much, about 10 minutes.
Mix up remaining ingredients and put in crock-pot or slow cooker, etc.
Add meatballs.
Heat on medium for 15 minutes. Turn temperature down to simmer/warm.
Get some toothpicks and enjoy!

title: no knead bread
directions: Combine warm water and yeast and stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add water and yeast mix to remaining ingredients. Gradually add 10 cups Pillsbury bread flour.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed.
Place in warm spot for 30 minutes.
Divide into 4 parts and put into 4 greased bread pans.
Cover with damp towel and let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Slice bread into thin sticks.
Roll in melted margarine, then in Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Simmer for 40 minutes or until the cucumbers turn clear.
Seal in quart size jars.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours before serving. Other flavors pie filling can be substituted.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Blend all ingredients (except coconut) in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in two 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat is slightly brown.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and heat thoroughly.
Turn into an 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut cheese into thin strips and sprinkle over meat. Top with biscuits and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: dill veggie dip
directions: Combine ingredients the day before serving.
Refrigerate until needed.
This recipe may be halved.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain. Add chili mix.
Stir until mixed together.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Stir while adding ingredients.
Add coffee to thin, until desired thickness. Simmer on medium for 2 to 3 minutes.
Then cook on low until ready to eat.
Add coffee when needed or soup to thicken.
Add crackers to taste!

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a dish.
Put cheese on top.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Simmer al the ingredients 20 minutes.
Pour apple mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust on and crimp edges.
Brush top with softened butter, flour and milk.
Cut a slash or two in middle of crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°. Sprinkle liberally with powdered sugar while still hot.
Best apple pie ever eaten.
The lemon juice makes the difference.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan.
Spread remaining tomato sauce over top of loaf. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Drain excess grease.
Cut loaf in half and continue baking for an additional 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in pieces, make both from wing tips.
Dip wing pieces in egg and then flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Arrange in casserole.
Combine broth, sugar, catsup, soy sauce and vinegar. Add Accent, pour over wings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Turn once during baking.
Serve with rice.

title: flavory pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat on foil and sprinkle soup mix on all sides.
Wrap in foil, sealing edges airtight with double fold.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake until desired doneness, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: johnnie masetta
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and soup.
Cook 30 minutes.
Season with seasonings and brown sugar.
Before removing from heat, add mushrooms and olives. Add to cooked noodles; mix well and put in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Place in hot oven 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 10 generously.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Cut chicken into small bite size pieces.
In a large skillet or wok, cook chicken in oil until tender.
Toss chicken frequently during cooking period.
Prepare pea pods by cutting off ends and removing strings.
Add pea pods, mushrooms and onion to chicken. Toss.
Continue cooking for 2 minutes.
Add bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Mix together bouillon, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, pepper and salt.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss.
Cover and cook until the sauce has thickened.
Stir in cashew nuts.
Serve with rice.
Yields 6 servings.
Fat:
None.
Oil per serving:
1 2/3 teaspoons.

title: potato-crusted sausage quiche
directions: Combine egg substitute, cottage cheese, flour, pepper and Tabasco sauce in a large bowl; stir to mix well.
Stir in the cheese, sausage, and scallions; set aside.
Coat a 9-inch deep-dish pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Slice the unpeeled potatoes 1/4-inch thick, and arrange the slices in a single layer over the bottom and sides of the pan to form a crust.
Pour egg mixture into the crust.

Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes, or until a sharp knife inserted into the center of the quiche comes out clean. Allow to cool at room temperature for 5 minutes before cutting into wedges and serving.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: alpine breakfast cereal
directions: Soak oats overnight in water.
Mix with all other ingredients.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time and beat well. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, pears and pecans.
This will be a thick batter.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.
(You can substitute apples for pears.)

title: auxiliary dip
directions: Measure and add all ingredients in order listed into mixing bowl.
Blend well with spoon.
Serve cold with chips or crackers.

title: biscuits with sour cream-romania(pesmeti cu smintina)
directions: Beat the sugar with egg yolks and whole eggs, add vanilla, sour cream, baking soda, and butter, mix well.

title: kahlua
directions: You will need 1 funnel, 1 large pot, 1 gallon jug with cap (preheated) and a paper coffee strainer.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put raisins in boiling water for softening.
Drain before putting in the rice pudding.
Boil rice and dash of salt; drain it.
Put into casserole dish, then add sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well, then add raisins.
Add milk.
Before you put into oven put cinnamon on top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Done when cake tester doesn't stick.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and press with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown around edge.

title: quick fixin' tuna supper
directions: In a large skillet, combine milk and flour.
Bring to a boil. Add Pasta Accents; cover and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in tuna.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini crunch
directions: Mix zucchini, apple juice, lemon juice and cinnamon; put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with flour, oleo, brown sugar and baking powder. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: harold's cajun chili
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup swiss cheese, sour cream, pepper, and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a 1 quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the rest of cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: hot fudge candy
directions: Cook for 1 minute on medium heat.

title: ella's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift flour and all other dry ingredients; add to other mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two well-prepared loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add cream and egg yolks; mix, then add salt and water.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Add meringue.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats; cover and let stand while mixing other ingredients, about 10 minutes.
Cream oleo, sugars and eggs together and add oatmeal mixture.
Mix thoroughly and mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown the onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add the chicken, celery, meat stock, soy sauce and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend together the cornstarch and cold water and stir into the chicken mixture.
Cook until thickened and clear.
Serve on chow mein noodles or rice.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Mix all ingredients but zucchini.
Lightly fold in zucchini last.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Cut into squares, then into triangles.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind together (or use food processor) the tomatoes, peppers, onions, salt and cabbage.
Let set.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and pickling spice.
Mix all together in a large pot. Cook over medium heat to a good boil; continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Pack into hot sterile jars and seal.
Good with meat or beans.

title: squash soup
directions: In small skillet, saute onion until soft.
Place onion, squash and broth in blender.
Blend until blended well.
Add flour and blend again just to mix.
Pour the mixture into saucepan.
Fold in half and half.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon of flour, salt and peppers (dry).
Toss to coat chicken.
Fry in oil 4 to 5 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine cinnamon, flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add zucchini and walnuts, mixing well.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef curry delicious
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving on wax paper, combine flour, salt and pepper. Roll meat in it.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; place in jar (whole).
Add ingredients per quart.
If vinegar mix doesn't fill jar, fill jar up with cold water.
Screw on lids; let stand for 2 or 3 months.

title: melissa's cucumbers
directions: Put sliced cucumbers in a container with a tight lid.
Pour vinegar over cucumbers to cover.
Place in fridge to chill.
Great with salads or all by themselves.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
Arrange potato wedges, peel side down, in 2 shallow baking pans.
Mix other ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a casserole.
Crush potato for the top.
Bake at 350°
until hot and bubbly about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and milk in large bowl.
Add cherry juice. Chop all other ingredients and add to bowl.
Top with pineapple slices.
Place in freezer for 3 hours.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Continue to mix in clean snow until you have the right consistency for ice cream.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook first six ingredients together until real thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix.
Then seal in hot jars.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake or microwave potatoes until tender.
While potatoes are hot, carefully slice in half, lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, keeping 8 of the best shells.
Mash the potato pulp with butter and cream.
Add Parmesan cheese and seasoned salt; beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Mound potatoes back into reserved shells and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° to 400° until piping hot and slightly browned on top.
Makes 8 potato halves.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
In a medium sized bowl, stir until blended, the vegetable soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise, then stir in spinach, water chestnuts (chopped) and chopped green onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and butter; add cabbage.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once or twice. After cabbage is cooked, add pimientos and soup; stir together. Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle in uncooked rice.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix soups and water together. Pour on top of chicken and rice.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese and pecans.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in mayonnaise, cucumber and onion.
Chill until set.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; let stand a few minutes.
Add the buttermilk.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Mix in the chopped nuts, flour, soda and salt.
Combine and stir until just blended.
Add the chopped dates.
Pour into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be stored in fridge for 6 weeks.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Add hot water to Jell-O, then add other ingredients.
Congeal.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk. Add baking powder to flour.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese nut rolls
directions: Spread first package of rolls in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, cheese, egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Spread other package of rolls on top.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Spread on top of rolls. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts and scant 1/4 cup sugar over egg white. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares the size of your choice.

title: soft clouds
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; whip with electric mixer until smooth.
Transfer to greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in jars or tins.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons to 3/4 cup boiling water or to desired strength.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ricearoni
directions: Cook rice until tender. Brown the beef lightly in butter in a large skillet. Add salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Drain rice and stir in meat mixture. Add sugar, ketchup and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Simmer 5 minutes.
Ready for serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into other mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab and corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon to crisp; set aside.
Leave about 2 tablespoons fat in pan.
Add butter; melt.
Saute (low) onion and celery 3 to 5 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir to mix.
Cook 1 minute on low.
Add half and half.
Bring to a boil.
Keep stirring then reduce to simmer (must boil to thicken).
Add crabmeat and corn (water and all) then add potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer between 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
Stir often.
Just before serving, stir in crumbled bacon.
Garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli, fettucini and cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Boil until the cubes dissolve.
Add noodles.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir in garlic and broccoli.
Cook about 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper. Makes 4 quarts.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Fry shells, a few at a time, in deep hot oil at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown; drain.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with Velveeta; broil until cheese spread begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, beating after each egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 4 layer pans or 1 tube pan for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Add enough milk to stick together for forming into balls.
In a double boiler, melt paraffin and chips.
Dip balls with toothpick.
Set on waxed paper to cool.

title: plunkin cake
directions: In large saucepan, heat all ingredients except rolls (do not boil).
Stir cut up rolls into mixture.
Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Set in cold oven overnight.
In the morning, leave rolls in the oven and turn on to 350°.
Bake about 40 minutes or until brown.
Let set about 5 minutes and turn onto plate.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Layer butter, sugar and pineapple evenly in cake pan. Pour cake mix evenly over top. Bake as directed on box.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake uncovered in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (or pan) at 325° for about 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and put in bottom of 2-quart Pyrex.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, cheese and eggs together.
Spread over broccoli.
Spoon soup over all this.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken queso spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Melt Ro-Tel and Velveeta together. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix all together and invite neighbors!

title: bean dip
directions: Mix in saucepan until cream cheese melts, then serve with chips.

title: low-fat cool whip delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and chill well.

title: totally texas cornbread
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Add corn, peppers and onion mixing well.
Stir in cheese.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan and spread with 1/2 of batter.
Spread ground beef over first layer of batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with green salad for a meal.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding corn bread mix last.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Mix and sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture; mix well. Add nuts and chocolate pieces; mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Chill for a short time.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: apple nog
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until fluffy and light.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and apple cider.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Add to spinach the bacon, eggs and onion.

title: baked stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make stuffing as directed on package for four servings. Wash and pat dry chicken breasts.
Put a small ball of stuffing in center of each breast.
Wrap meat around. Secure at the bottom with a toothpick if necessary.
Cover tops of breasts lightly with olive oil and sprinkle spices over breasts. Cook uncovered for 40 minutes or until done.
Good with gravy and mashed potatoes.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Cube and soak bread in milk and half and half.
Crush with hands until well mixed.
Then add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins and stir well.
Pour melted margarine in bottom of thick baking pan and bake at 350° until firm.
Let cool.
Cube to serve and put into individual serving dishes.
Serve with hot Rum or Whiskey Sauce.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine
sugar	and cornstarch.
Slowly add water while stirring.
Bring
to
a boil and cook until clear.	Add strawberry gelatin.
Cool slightly.
Pour over strawberries placed in baked shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Mix together and simmer for 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: hamburger in a hurry
directions: Layer all ingredients, except mushroom soup.
Pour mushroom soup over the top, plus about 1/4 can of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into ball.
Decorate with pecan halves. May sprinkle with paprika.

title: lettuce and pea salad
directions: Break up lettuce and make a layer in bottom of dish, then a layer of diced red onion, then diced pepper, then layer of peas. Repeat, then cover with mayonnaise and sprinkle with cheese and refrigerate for 24 hours before using.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: tuna dish casserole
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil in saucepan and pour over rice in casserole dish.
Grate Cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut-pecan cake
directions: With mixer, mix cake mix, water, eggs and oil.
Stir in coconut cream frosting with spoon.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325 - 350 approximately 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 -15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: crab soup
directions: Mix 4 cans together
and heat.	Add curry powder.
Just before serving, add sherry.
Easy and delicious!

title: reese's cookies
directions: Make peanut butter crackers.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler over hot water.
Dip crackers to coat thoroughly.
Place on wax paper until dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy stew beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in deep casserole.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bacon and peanuts. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add bacon and peanuts and mix.

title: chunky brownies with a crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup flour and sugar. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: creamy corn pudding(microwave recipe)
directions: Place egg into greased casserole dish and beat well with fork. Stir in all the other ingredients. Place into microwave oven and cook for 6 minutes at Medium-defrost.
Stir well after 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven (Medium-defrost) and cook for 7 to 10 more minutes, giving 1/4 turn after 4 minutes.
(When done, center will be just barely wet.)

title: chocolate scooteroos
directions: *May use 1/2 bag chocolate and 1/2 bag butterscotch chips instead of 1 bag chocolate chips.

title: butterflied coconut shrimp
directions: Slit shrimp along curved side, cutting almost through.
Place on paper towel. Heat 2-inches of oil in a saucepan to 350°. Combine flour, salt and dry mustard in small bowl.
Beat egg and cream of coconut in small bowl.
In third bowl, combine coconut and bread crumbs.
Dip shrimp in flour mixture, then egg mixture, then coconut mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to cook.

title: caramel chip cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add egg, vanilla and shortening.
Blend until smooth.
Add nuts and caramel chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tuna sour cream filling
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Use as sandwich filling or spread for crackers.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Put tea bags in 1 cup hot water for 3 minutes.
Squeeze excess from tea bags into water.
Add remaining ingredients to the tea. Mix well and freeze.
Add 7-Up, Wink or 4% when ready to serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat all on medium heat except vanilla.
Reduce heat and stir constantly until thickened (about 5 minutes), then add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour over ice cream, brownies, etc.

title: honey basting sauce for barbecue
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil.
Do not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Use for basting or for marinating.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Put crab meat in blender or food processor and chop very fine. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, soup and beans.
Layer in a casserole dish the Doritos, meat mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbling.

title: noodles with pesto sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except spaghetti. Beat with fork to combine thoroughly.
Place well-drained hot spaghetti in large bowl.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and toss lightly to coat thoroughly.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave turkey divan(yields 4 servings)
directions: In a small glass bowl, combine soup and milk and cook on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth and set aside.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix; divide dough into 2 parts.	Roll out each piece of dough and spread with
sausage;
roll
up
like
jellyroll and chill overnight.	Slice crosswise.
Place
on baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: osgood pie
directions: Put sugar in bowl, then break in the eggs and beat well. Add butter, vinegar, spice, dates and nuts. Pour into uncooked crust. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Shred and grate a cucumber (pour off the water).
Add 2 squirts of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix rest of the ingredients in the bowl and chill.

title: shrimp thermidor
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in shrimp.
Place in well-greased dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or longer if cold.
Serve over rice.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim any fat and gristle from flank steak. Cut meat with grain into thin slices (partially freeze first to make slicing easier). Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak strips. Marinate in refrigerator about 15 hours. Squeeze marinade from the meat by rolling strips with rolling pin.
Place meat on baking sheets or directly on oven racks and dry in a 175° oven for 9 hours, turning once.
If using rack, place foil under to catch any drippings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring the sugar, Karo and water to a boil.
Add the raw peanuts or pecans.
Cook until 300°.
Remove.
Add the vanilla and baking soda quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet (with margarine).
Cool; break apart.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil.
Add rice and both packages Lipton chicken noodle soup mix.
Stir, cover tightly and set aside.

title: real fudge pie(my moma's recipe)
directions: Mix all
ingredients and bake at 325° for 35 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: agape class breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter bread and cube.
Spread bread on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sausage, cheese, bell pepper, onion and mushroom over bread.
Mix eggs, mustard, milk and salt.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in two unbaked pie shells.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add chili seasoning. Add beans, Ro-Tel, cream and Velveeta.
Heat until creamy and cheese melts.
Put mixture on top of tortilla chips.
Then top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and onions.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Drain pineapple well and mix with pie filling. Add condensed milk and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before using.
Serve over angel food cake. Ingredients should all be ice cold before mixing.

title: bobalky(a slovak christmas eve specialty)
directions: Into a mixing bowl place butter, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk; let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Add enough flour to make a soft elastic dough.
Turn onto a floured board and knead.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk (1 to 1 1/2 hours) in a warm place, free from drafts. Punch dough down with fingertips and let rise again (about 45 minutes).
Toss lightly on floured board, knead and shape into a roll (like a pipe) about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cut with edge of teaspoon into small pieces and let rise for 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
When cool, break and place in colander.
Pour boiling water over bobalky.
Place in serving dish, mix with poppy seed* and melted butter and serve.

title: cream of broccoli or cauliflower and cheese soup
directions: Heat 2 cups of water to boil.
Add vegetables and lemon juice. Cook until tender.
Put through food processor to smooth out. Set aside.
In pan, heat margarine; add flour.
Slowly add 2 1/2 cups water.
Heat to boil.
Add vegetables, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Heat until bubbly.
Add whipping cream and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.

title: steak creole
directions: Brown steak in a pan.
Drain.
Remove any grease from pan. Put steak pieces back in pan.
Add bell pepper strips and onion slices.
Mix tomato-rice soup with 1 can water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over steak, peppers and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and cook over low heat or simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cream banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice. In a large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat until well blended. Chill 3 minutes. Fold in whipping cream and pineapple. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture in a 2 1/2 quart round glass serving bowl. Top with one-third each of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layers, ending with pudding. Chill thoroughly.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix the sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in greased muffin pans.
Makes 4 dozen muffins.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion (I don't cook onion with the broccoli. I just add onion when I add everything else.) according to package directions.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°
for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Disjoint chicken wings, discarding bony tips.
Arrange meatier parts in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until sugar and butter dissolve.
Pour over wings, marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Bake in marinade at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once and spooning marinade over chicken occasionally.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot or cold.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes. Blend next 3 ingredients.
Combine with apple mixture.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Mix with apple mixture.
Stir in raisins. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: spinach balls delight
directions: Cook, chop and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° on a cookie sheet for about 15 minutes.
Serves 15 or more.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers, onions and cabbage.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt and boil mixture 5 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: dee's banana nut bread
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Mix well the rest of the ingredients with the creamed mixture.
Cook in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or use 2 loaf pans and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is kept well in the refrigerator for several days.

title: forty garlic chicken
directions: Place garlic under the skin of the chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drizzle with a little olive oil.
Bake at 450° to 500° for one hour in covered casserole dish.
Serve with French or sourdough bread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Season to taste.
Place layers, in order given, in a one-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425° or until bubbles.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: happy day cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes; cover with the fine bread crumbs or flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in butter.
Serve hot.

title: gourmet ark valley cooked goose
directions: Preparation, cooking and serving instructions:
Preheat oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Place thawed goose on cedar board approximately 12 X 18 inches, 1/4 to 1 inch thick.
Rub bird down with butter or margarine to insure seasonings stick to carcass. Season bird with:
Garlic salt, basil, poultry seasoning, and seasoning salt.
Season both inside and out.
Stovetop stuffing optional inside carcass.
Place goose on Cedar board on middle rack of oven.
After one hour remove and squeeze with fresh lemon. Place back in oven and gradually increase oven temperature to 425°. Cook an additional hour and thirty minutes after squeezing with lemon juice.
Remove from oven and let cool approximately 15 minutes.
Last step, throw the bird away and eat the cedar board.

title: old favorite walnut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl; add walnuts and raisins or dates.
To egg, add milk and melted shortening.
Beat into flour mixture.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 60 to 70 minutes or until done when tested.

title: cheese and onion potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Chill until firm.
Peel and shred. Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake uncovered in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frozen banana split dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add 2 cups of flour and the sugar. Work in remaining flour and knead.
Shape and place on a sprayed cookie sheet.
Mix the egg and water; brush on.
Add salt and bake at 425° for 6 to 15 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Half eggs lengthwise, mash yolks in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to yolks and blend well.
Fill egg halves with mixture and serve.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit well.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, sherry, flour and butter.
Cook until thick as heavy cream, stirring constantly. Arrange fruit in layers in a casserole pan, placing a layer of peaches, then a layer of pears, then pineapple.
Scatter the apple rings in each layer for color.
In center of each pineapple slice, place a cherry.
Pour the sauce over fruit.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, take out of refrigerator 30 minutes, then bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: meatless chili(diet)
directions: Spray pot with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes.
Add water and next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve with some sour cream on top.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: el rancho casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugars, oil and eggs.
Stir in baking soda and powder, salt, flour, oats, coconut, cornflakes, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies; bake for 10 to 12 minutes for crunchy cookies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix
all
together and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until "tests" done with toothpick.

title: hamburger stuffing hot dish]
directions: Put hamburger in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Slice onion over it.
Prepare stuffing according to directions; layer over onion.
Mix the water with the soups and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or microwave about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snowball salad
directions: Put cold water in gelatin.
Add boiling water and pineapple, then sugar and lemon juice.
Add 1 Dream Whip (mix as directed) and 3/4 of coconut; mix all.
Crumble cake and other ingredients in long pan.
Put other Dream Whip, coconut and cherries over salad.

title: cindy's mock caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear or cut.
Place into a large salad bowl.
Sprinkle lettuce with a generous amount of the cheeses and croutons.
Just before serving, toss with salad dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: billyle's blue
directions: Combine cheese and buttermilk to a paste; season with Tabasco sauce and stir in Blue cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: chick pea soup
directions: Brown beef (or pork). Add water to meat. Add onion and celery. Simmer for 3 hours. Discard onion and celery. Add chick peas, carrots, potatoes and sausage. Simmer for 2 hours. Add salt & pepper to taste.
Better the next day.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken with all ingredients except onion rings. Place in a low baking dish, approximately 13 x 9-inch pan/glass dish.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and top dish with onion rings and continue at 350° for additional 15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine until golden. Combine soup, water and Cheez Whiz.
Thaw broccoli or cook slightly with celery and onion (if pieces are large).
Prepare rice and set aside.

title: baked fish
directions: Arrange fillets in greased baking dish.
Cover with milk; dot with butter.
Then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Serve with lemon, butter or parsley, if desired.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup juice. Chop cherries. Stir together gelatins and 2 cups boiling water until dissolved. Stir in reserved cherry juice, sugar, wine and lemon juice. Stir in cherries. Pour half of the mixture into a lightly greased 10-cup ring mold or Bundt pan. Chill 2 hours or until almost set.

title: **holiday lizzies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Flour fruit and nuts with 1/2 of flour.
Add remaining flour, soda, wine and milk to creamed mixture.
Then add floured fruit and nuts to dough and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake in slow oven (300°) for 25 minutes or less.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serve over buns.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine all above ingredients & add dressing.

title: new fudge cream pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Gradually stir in canned milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 4 minutes.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks; return all to pan.

title: rice salad
directions: In large bowl, toss all ingredients to mix.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs on high until thick and light.
Add sugar gradually; then add the next three ingredients.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 2 loaves or 1 tube pan or 1 Bundt pan.

title: melba's delight
directions: Combine and mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Pat in the bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or lightly brown on edges.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix instant pudding with 3 cups of milk and spread over ingredients, then top with extra Cool Whip left in container.
Refrigerate.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water. Stir to dissolve and boil to 310° on candy thermometer (crack stage). Add flavoring and color. Pour onto foil lined with powdered sugar (thick layer). Cool slightly and cut with sharp scissors into squarish shapes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix soup and broth (and vegetables if used) together; pour over chicken.
Cut margarine into flour until crumbly.
Add milk.
Drizzle evenly over chicken. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve hot from the oven.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar; press firmly into pie pan.
Whip cream; add lemon juice and Eagle Brand. Whip until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour into crust and chill several hours.

title: greek herbed yogurt and cucumber
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with pita, as a salad, on lettuce or as a dip with crackers.

title: rice delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and hamburger in skillet until hamburger is done.
Season to taste.
Add water and celery; simmer for 5 minutes.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix in rice and soups.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion shell
directions: Cut
a large onion in half (not cross section).
Remove the inside
sections,
leaving	a cup 2 sections thick.
Fill with an egg or hamburger and place on bed of coals to cook.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In medium saucepan, bring the water to a boil.
Stir in the soup mix and boil for 5 minutes. With fork, quickly stir in the egg.
If you want your soup thick, mix well 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water and put in the soup, stirring well.

title: cheeseburger pie(lite recipe)
directions: Mix sauce, onion, pepper and spices and cook until tender. Add small amount of water if needed.
Mix turkey or beef (cooked), rice and half of cheese.
Pour in casserole.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes.
Extra cheese may be used if preferred.

title: i-45 cake
directions: Combine butter, 1 egg and cake mix; spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked creamed corn and peas
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter. Saut onion and celery until golden. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, basil and sugar. Mix well. Gradually add milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Mix peas and corn in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Pour milk sauce over top, mixing lightly. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Blend with bread crumbs and cheese. Sprinkle on mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
