directions: Combine chicken, celery, 1/2 of cheese, onion, lemon juice, seasonings and enough mayonnaise to moisten; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole; top with combined remaining cheese and chips.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except Cheez Whiz.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Let set half an hour before eating.

title: rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Then add your yeast to warm water (stir; let set).
Then add milk and yeast mixture to first ingredients.
Add flour and knead.
Put in greased bowl and let it rise double in size, then mix into roll. Let rise and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or make pizza shells and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir sugar and flour into corn.
Add egg and mix well.
Add melted margarine.
Microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Microwave 5 more minutes, or until thick.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter Crisco, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls of dough in this mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove to cooling racks.

title: garlic pork roast
directions: With sharp knife, cut deep pocket between each rib on meaty side of roast.
Combine green pepper, green onion, celery and garlic.
Season roast with salt and cayenne pepper, then stuff garlic mixture into pockets cut in roast; pack firmly.
Place roast rib side down in shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 3 hours or until meat thermometer reads 170°.
(Thermometer should be inserted before roast is put in oven if one is used.)
Let stand 15 minutes before carving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Bring chicken broth, soup and black pepper to boil.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put chicken and mixed vegetables.
Pour broth and soup mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Mix together the flour, milk and margarine; spoon over top of chicken, vegetables and broth mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 500° oven.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of concentrate with cornstarch in small saucepan; heat remaining concentrate.
Blend in cornstarch mixture. Stir constantly until thickened and smooth.
Stir in margarine and cinnamon.
Pour over apples.
Toss gently to coat.
Pour mixture in bottom crust.
Cover with top crust.
Cut vents; brush top with margarine or milk.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon.
Bake for 50 minutes at 400°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with grated cheese and crushed Ritz crackers or you can use fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp or crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, sweet pepper and celery in oleo until wilted. Add soup and shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add raw rice, Ro-Tel, Worcestershire sauce, salt, green onion and parsley. Pour in large casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt bacon drippings in saucepan or skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and Minute rice (right from the package).
Cook and stir over high heat until all are lightly browned.
Add hot water, Hunt's tomato sauce and seasonings,
Mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil, cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 delicious servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Mix well. Combine rind, juice, butter and enough water to make 3/4 cup mixture.
Beat in egg. Pour over dry ingredients and mix in enough to dampen.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together gently, just until flour is wet.
Add one 15 ounce box of Raisin Bran.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 6 hours or up to 3 weeks.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, eggs, Ricotta, parsley, basil, Romano, Parmesan, Italian seasoning, spinach and carrot.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and onion powder

title: cherry pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 2 large pie crust lined pie pans.

title: texas ranch chicken
directions: Microwave chicken 4 minutes.
Cut into small pieces.
Heat the soup, tomatoes and broth together.
In 2-quart casserole, place a layer of tortillas, a layer of chicken, then soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (uncovered). Lower heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Beat well the margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon, then add the flour and baking powder and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased baking sheet (15 x 11-inch).
Mark off 20 to 24 imaginary squares and drop blueberry filling (drained if juicy) by teaspoon onto each square.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
As soon as removed from oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar (use a strainer for sprinkling).
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 20 to 24 squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Stir sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Separate eggs. Pour the milk with the sugar mixture, saving a little to stir with egg yolks.
Add egg yolks into mixture; stir well. Cook until thickened. Remove from fire and add butter, vanilla and 1/2 can coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Spread over pie.
Sprinkle rest of coconut on top. Put into oven and slightly brown coconut.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp traviata
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, cutting down back to butterfly.
Mix egg and milk.
Mix bread crumbs and seasonings together.
Dip shrimp in egg wash then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Melt butter in saute pan.
Saute shrimp until brown.
Remove to warm platter.
Add sherry and lemon juice to pan and stir with wooden spoon to deglaze pan.
Cook down slightly, then pour over shrimp.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add butter, sugar and egg.
Stir until well blended.
Gradually add flour, mixing well after each addition.
Continue beating until well blended.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, about 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 rolls.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Add flour and mix until well blended. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, gradually adding sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and beat again.
Sift and measure flour and add salt and baking powder.
Sift together.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture, adding dry ingredients alternately with pineapple juice. Beat until smooth after each addition.

title: string beans with lemon(4 servings)
directions: Rinse the beans and drain them.
Put them into a saucepan with water to cover and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes or until tender, but a trifle firm.
Drain the beans and return them to the hot saucepan.
Add the butter and sprinkle with lemon juice, parsley and pepper.
Toss.
Sprinkle with lemon zest. Serve hot.

title: allen's best boiled crawfish
directions: Add all seasonings (onions, garlic, orange, lemons, Cajun Land seasoning and Tabasco sauce) to 1/3 of a large propane crawfish pot of water; bring to boil.
Add potatoes and cook for 3 minutes. Add crawfish, bring to boil, hard boil for 5 to 7 minutes, then add corn and hot dogs.
Turn off heat and soak 20 minutes.
Serve with ketchup, cocktail sauce and crackers!

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder, then vanilla.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together.
(Don't overcook macaroni.)
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix and melt cheese and soups.
Alternate layers of chips, chicken and cheese sauce.
Top with some crushed chips.
Put in oven and heat.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Get 2 pieces of bread.
Get some cheese (2 pieces).
Put some butter on the cheese.
Put some mayonnaise on the cheese.
Put the bread on top and bottom.
Put the bread on top and bottom.
Put it in the oven at 20° for 15 minutes.
Take it out and eat it.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat together butter and cream cheese.
Stir in the kernel corn, cream-style corn, chillies and onion; mix well.
(Tastes better if onions are sauteed.) Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: easy low-fat dessert
directions: Cut the angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Open the two cans of cherry pie filling.
Mix the pudding according to package directions.
Layer in a glass straight-sided bowl:
1/2 of the angel food cake, 1/2 of the pudding and 1 can of pie filling. Make a second layer of the remainder of the cake, pudding and pie filling.
Refrigerate for about an hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together and pour over veggies.
If making day before, don't put dressing on until next day when you are ready to serve it.
I use about 2 1/2 tablespoons white vinegar, but other kinds will do.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until creamed.
Add flour, salt, soda, vanilla and cinnamon to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Stir cocoa, margarine and vanilla with spoon.
Add sugar, eggs and milk and stir until well blended.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add beef and green pepper; brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, bay leaf and chili powder.
Cover; cook 1 hour. Add beans and water and simmer 5 minutes.

title: beef tips over noodles
directions: Brown meat in a large, heavy bottom skillet.
Add diced tomatoes, green pepper, onion, garlic, beef base and 1/2 of the water. Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Mix cornstarch and remaining water and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Serve meat mixture over hot, cooked noodles.

title: crispy oven fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip chicken in batter.
Place in greased shallow pan.
Cook 1/2 hour at 400°, turn and bake 1/2 hour on other side.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour a little at a time.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into a floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips.
Combine flour and sour cream.
Stir in bouillon granules, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
This makes approximately 3 gallons and is very refreshing.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix lime Jell-O, cream cheese and pineapple along with hot water.
Chill until slightly set.
Whip the cream; fold in the Jell-O mixture.
Chill until time to serve.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flour.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Leave in oven another 15 minutes with oven off.
Take out and leave in pan another 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through. Serve with sweet pepper strips, broccoli flowerets or crackers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and form into loaf or balls.
Roll in crushed corn flakes. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Pour sauce over top.

title: chili seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until evenly distributed.
Spoon mixture onto a 6-inch square of aluminum foil to make airtight.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Makes 1 package (about 1/4 cup) of chili seasoning mix.

title: herb butter
directions: Mix in mixer or blender.
Great to saute veggies, or use on popcorn or French bread.
Use in place of salt.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in large mixer bowl at high speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour, then sugar, mixing until well blended.
By hand, stir in frosting mix and nuts.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar and then the other ingredients.
Freeze as directed on your home freezer.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients into a bottle type container.
Shake well. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in hot water.
When it begins to set, add the fruit, celery and pimentos which have been marinated in the vinegar and salt.
Put into two individual molds and let stand until set.
Unmold and serve on crisp lettuce leaf.
Yield:
2 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 20. One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Blend in pumpkin and oil. Fold in nuts. Pour into small greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: homemade pimentos
directions: Remove stem ends and seeds and cut peppers in half.
Cover 3 times with boiling water, allowing water to stand 3 minutes each time before draining.
Pack peppers in jar.
Boil ingredients for 10 minutes.
Fill jars to overflowing and seal.
Process pint cans 15 minutes.
One quart brine is enough for 3 pints.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, Cream of Wheat, egg, onion, pepper and all seasonings.
Add 1 cup tomato juice.
Mix together lightly.
Pack in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350°, basting with remaining liquid.
Cook 45 minutes to one hour, depending on the thickness of the loaf.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Cream together oleo, oil, sugar and egg yolks.
Add buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat 5 egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in 4 layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and spread Chinese noodles on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in 3 sticks the size of 1/2 dollar.
Place in the refrigerator for 24 hours wrapped in foil.
Then take out of refrigerator and unwrap.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Feeds 10 to 15.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Clean, slice and drain strawberries.
Mix everything together except berries.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add berries and pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill.

title: frog eyed salad
directions: Cook Acini De Pepe.
In heavy saucepan, beat egg with wire whisk until foamy.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and reserved pineapple juice.
Over low heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
In a large bowl, combine Acini De Pepe with egg mixture. Chill thoroughly, about 1 hour.
Stir in pineapple, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream. Cover and chill.
Stir before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, onion, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar in a pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage and 1/2 cup water in casserole, cover and microwave 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix meat, egg, rice, onion, spices, pepper sauce and 1/4 cup of tomato sauce.
Place 1/4 cup mixture on each leaf and roll up.
Mix remaining sauce, paste, water, sugar and basil.
Pour over rolls and cover.
Microwave at Medium-high for 25 minutes, moving rolls from center to side halfway through.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add amount of water each can of fruit juice calls for.
When ready to serve, add Sprite and ice cubes.

title: green salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top and mix lightly into salad.
Just before serving, add Italian dressing. Toss and serve.

title: toffy squares(yield: 2 dozen or more)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: oriental steak
directions: Cut meat in one-inch squares.
Marinate in soy sauce and water for two hours.
Saute green peppers, onions and mushrooms in margarine in a skillet.
In larger skillet or Dutch oven, add everything together; cover and simmer slowly for about 2 or 2 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Layer sliced zucchini on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sliced tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle spices over tomatoes.
Repeat until pan is almost full.
Sprinkle heavily with cheeses until pan is covered.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until vegetables are cooked through.
Garnish with more cheese before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: emily's, janie's and mary whilden's favorite pancakes(from better homes and gardens junior cookbook)
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Heat griddle.
Sprinkle a few drops of water on the griddle; if it jumps, the griddle is hot enough.
Measure 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
When bubbles cover surface of pancake, turn over.
Makes 7 to 8 pancakes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first three ingredients, then cut in shortening.
Beat water, vinegar and egg together and add to other ingredients until moist.

title: grandma's cornstarch pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan over medium-high heat. Slowly add milk, cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Stir constantly so as not to let burn.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter/margarine.
Beat until smooth.
For chocolate pudding, simply add cocoa to sugar and cornstarch mixture before adding milk to cook.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put in casserole dish.
Add syrup, bacon bits and broiled frankfurters.
Mix all together and top off with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: harvest pumpkin pie
directions: Combine apple butter, pumpkin, brown sugar, salt and spices; add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add cream and mix thoroughly. Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 2 greased 8-inch pie plates. Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 minutes. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: prize winning meatloaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pack firmly in loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hr. & 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in top of a 2-quart double boiler. Meanwhile, sift powdered sugar and dry milk. Stir together corn syrup, water and vanilla into chocolate mixture over boiling water. Blend in sifted dry ingredients in two additions, stirring until mixture is well blended and smooth. Remove from boiling water. Mix in nuts or marshmallows. Turn into 8-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: camper's smores
directions: Place Hershey's chocolate on 1 piece of graham cracker. Roast marshmallows
over	coals
until
golden
brown.
Place marshmallow on top of Hershey's
chocolate and cap with second graham cracker.
Mash flat while
hot.
For
variety,
you may also use peanut butter rather than Hershey's chocolate in this recipe.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; add soup and cheese to rice.
Saute onions in butter; add broccoli to onions.
Pour broccoli and then rice into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt mattie winn's tea cakes(born february 12, 1876)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, salt and baking powder; mix.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: coleslaw
directions: Grate first 4 ingredients and mix together.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and stir into the cabbage mixture.

title: tena's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes as on package directions.
Drain. Beat egg and mix with mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onions, salt, pepper and cheese.

title: frozen chocolate pie
directions: Mix soft ice cream in large bowl.
(Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips if you can't find them in the ice cream.)
Place in prepared pie crust.
Pour 1/4 chocolate syrup over it.
Freeze until very firm.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, lemon juice and rind, cornstarch, milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick, cool slightly and add sour cream.
Stir.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue and put on pie.
Brown in oven.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise, removing stem ends, seeds and membranes.
Immerse peppers into boiling water for three minutes. Sprinkle insides with salt.
Invert on paper towels to drain well.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in saucepan with salt and water until tender (6 to 8 minutes); drain.
Add onion, milk and margarine.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with buttered crumbs (from toast). Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add salad dressing, Salad Supreme, onion and bell pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir or toss 2 or 3 times.
Add tomato and avocado just before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add puree, spices and water.
Cook slowly for 1 to 2 hours.
While sauce is cooking, prepare eggplant.
Slice 1 large eggplant thin and dust each slice with flour.
Beat 4 eggs with 1/2 cup milk.
Dip each slice of eggplant in egg.
Fry each slice slowly in oil on each side.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
When done, line a 9 x 13-inch pan with sauce.
Place eggplant over bottom and sprinkle with Romano cheese and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Keep doing this, alternating layers.
Top with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: omi's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute chopped onion in margarine.
Add flour to make paste. Add water and tomato paste.
Stir and add additional water until you have a sauce the consistency you like.
Serve over rigatoni or large macaroni shells.
Sauce serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil 10 minutes in a Dutch oven.
Drain. Dice potatoes; add onions, celery, celery seed, celery salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a large skillet.
Add beef cubes to meat and onions.
Then add mushrooms, sliced.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together in separate bowl.
Add soup mixture last.
Simmer on low heat while noodles are cooking.
Serve Hamburger Stroganoff over hot noodles with a green salad and hot rolls.
"Enjoy."

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in salt.
Add tomato soup, mushrooms and green beans.
Mix.
Top with mashed potatoes. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Pour cherry pie filling in the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown or when top is crisp.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil.
Brush slices with mixture.
Put remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and browned at the edges.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon ice
directions: Mix sugar and lemon juice.
Add mixture to ice cold milk. Pour into refrigerator tray or stainless steel bread pan.
Put in freezer.
Remove tray when ice is partially frozen.
Beat smooth and return to freezer until solid.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes 15 minutes; peel and cut in half lengthwise. Place in buttered baking dish.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes, basting often.

title: smothered cubed steak
directions: Pound into steak a mixture of self-rising flour, salt and garlic salt.
Fry steak quickly on all sides in 3 tablespoons hot oil.
Remove; cook all of the steak.
Add more oil if needed.
When all of the steak is cooked, remove from pan.
Add 3 tablespoons self-rising flour; brown well, adding oil if needed.
Mix water or milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into browned flour; cook until a thin gravy.
Add more milk if needed.
Return browned steak to gravy; simmer for 30 minutes.
May add chopped onion to meat before the simmering starts.
Serve with rice, green beans and garden salad.

title: squash casserole(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Boil squash and onion until squash is tender; drain.
Mix onion, soup and squash.
In casserole dish, grease and crumble (1 pack out of box) Ritz crackers in bottom, then layer 1/2 of soup mixture, layer 1/2 of cheese, layer crackers, soup and cheese again.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: secret fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in heavy pan; mix well to prevent lumping of cocoa. Add condensed milk and milk.

Cook on medium-high heat, stirring constantly, to a rolling boil. Reduce heat and add baking soda. Stir until mixture stops excessive bubbling. Add butter and continue to boil 13 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, to firm soft ball stage when tested in cold water (about 238°).
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes. Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens and loses its glossiness. Add nuts or coconut (if desired) and continue stirring until very thick.
Pour into buttered pan or drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: hawaiian sheet cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cooled, frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: taffy tan fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; bring to boil.
Stir 5 minutes over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan until firm.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook until it thickens. Stir in cream cheese until well blended.
Cool.
Add apples.
Pour into dish.
Cover with Cool Whip, top with pecans and chill.

title: chili
directions: Soak dry beans in water overnight.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours; only if canned beans are used). When using canned beans (2 one pound cans), drain liquid.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix by package directions using 2 cups milk. Add brown sugar, butter and vanilla.
Cover surface of pudding with waxed paper; chill.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
top with whipped cream.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into a ball; roll in chopped nuts.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, parsley and pineapple slices.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine	in
oven.
Sprinkle
crumbs
over
margarine.
Mix together and press in pan.	Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly
with chocolate chips, walnuts and coconut.	Press down firmly.
Bake
for	25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool
thoroughly
before
cutting.	Store loosely, covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 bars.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
When cooled, dice potatoes with skins into an 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add cubed Velveeta and Cheddar cheese.
(I like a lot of cheese.)
You may use only one kind of cheese if preferred.
Crumble fried bacon into potato and cheese mixture. Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.

title: grandma's pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs; drain juice from pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and juice; cook over slow heat until thick.
Pour over bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add vanilla.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Pop the corn 1/3 cup at a time (make 3 poppings).
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil and let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir mixture into popcorn well.
Put into a large pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool and break apart.
Nuts may be added.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles.
Cook in saucepan until cheese melts.
Cook the noodles and mix with other.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan; cover with crushed potato chips.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix in enough mayo or Miracle Whip to cover ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Wash vegetables.
Slant cut carrots and celery.
Chop cabbage. Heat oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
Add onion chunks and beef.
Saute until meat is done.
Add all vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Add salt and soy sauce. Cover.
Cook 1 minute.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss salad and serve with your favorite dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 large servings.

title: fettoosh salad(syrian)
directions: Roast bread; cube it and set aside.
Wash all vegetables. Break parsley and mint leaves off stems.
Slice carrots and cucumbers.
Cut tomatoes into chunks.
Tear lettuce into pieces and chop onions.
Mix all together.
Add lemon juice, olive oil, salt, sumaq (if available) and garlic.
Add roasted bread 15 minutes before serving.
Mix well.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: orange pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Cut brownies into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl the brownies, strawberries, sliced bananas and Cool Whip. Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Peel potatoes and cut lengthwise into quarters.
Cut each quarter into three strips.
In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Roll potato strips in melted butter, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Pour any remaining butter over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Shake all ingredients in plastic bag until potatoes are coated evenly.
Place on shallow roasting pan.
Stir occasionally until golden brown in a 450° oven.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until the mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water.
Stir quickly with a fork until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Roll dough into a ball. Roll between waxed paper or roll on floured board.
Roll until 1 inch larger than the pie plate all the way around.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; blend together orange peel, cream cheese, yogurt, mayonnaise and spice.
Fold fruit cocktail and orange sections into cream cheese mixture.
Cut bananas lengthwise into quarters.
Arrange banana slices on lettuce lined plates. Spoon fruit-cheese mixture in center.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and refrigerate until serving time. This luscious colorful banana split salad is full of delicious surprises.

title: mom's breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Grease pizza pan.
Cover the bottom of the pan with the crescent dough.
Next, sprinkle the sausage over the dough.
Mix 3/4 c. milk and 4 eggs together adding salt & pepper.
After mixing, pour it over the sausage and dough.
Sprinkle 2 cups cheese on top.
Cook at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: molasses crisp
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Roll into marble sized balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut chip chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together egg, peanut butter and sugar.
Stir in baking soda, vanilla and chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter or margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: apple crumble
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place apples in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Mix flour, butter and brown sugar.
Crumble this mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: macaroni deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni and add to mixture.
Top with grated cheese. This amount makes 4 to 6 servings.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Cream the oil and sugar together.
Add egg and beat until blended.
Beat in vanilla and applesauce.
Stir in the dry ingredients.
Add oats and raisins to mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni-kidney bean casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
In large bowl combine macaroni, tomatoes, beans, pepper, onion, tomato juice, bacon and drippings.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until crumbs are slightly brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cut fine onion, pepper and celery; steam together.
Fry hamburger until nearly done, then add vegetables, seasonings and soup.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: In pot on stove, bring to soft boiled stage.
Add pecans; stir until sugared.
Pour onto waxed paper.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix together meat, tomatoes and beans; set aside. Lightly grease glass baking dish.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheeses. Makes two layers.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; continue stirring until mixture comes to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla extract; cool.
Add confectioners sugar, beating well after each addition, until of spreading consistency.
Fills and frost top and sides of two 8-inch or 9-inch layers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into crust that has been baked.
Beat egg whites and put on top, then brown.

title: indian corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, corn meal, oil, egg and garlic salt together.
Stir together cheese and chilies in separate bowl.
Layer corn mixture, cheese mix, corn mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats; let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, sugar, Bake-Rite and salt.
Add dry ingredients, eggs and oil to oats mixture, stirring until combined.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Bake.

title: peanut butter dealies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into a square pan. Spread melted chocolate chips on top and let harden.
Cut and enjoy.

title: "red slaw"
directions: Mix finely grated cabbage, chopped green peppers, tomatoes and sweet relish in a large bowl. Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper until sugar melts. Pour over cabbage mixture. Stir. Seal and refrigerate. Better the 2nd day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add pumpkin, eggs and water and mix together. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts and raisins. Grease and flour two loaf pans or use three 1 pound coffee tins, filled over 1/2 from top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is done. Depending on your oven it may take longer.

title: coffee coffee cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, adding raisins last.
Set aside; prepare Streusel.

title: bread serving bowl
directions: An attractive way to serve chicken legs or chicken salad.

title: easy dessert
directions: Pour over this 1/2 pint medium whipping cream and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Before using, whip cream and spread over angel cake.
Place back in refrigerator and let stand until ready to serve.

title: strawberry jam recipe easy 3-step
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.
Set aside 10 minutes. Stir Sure-Jell with water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan in given order.
Alternate eggs and tomatoes in rows on top of salad.
Cover pan tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: bonnie's broccoli salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces and combine with crumbled bacon, cheese and chopped onion.

title: brownies
directions: Melt together over hot water, chocolate squares and shortening.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in the nuts.
Spread in well-greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until top has dull crust, 30 to 35 minutes.
A slight imprint will be left when top is touched lightly with finger.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.
Frost, if desired, before cutting.
Yields 16 two-inch squares.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except flour and pour in well of flour.
Beat until very stiff.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: peanut rice krispies candy
directions: Spread Rice Krispies and salted peanuts in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Stir constantly over medium heat until boiling.
Add peanut butter and vanilla to sugar and syrup.
Pour over Rice Krispies and peanuts and mix well.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: rose rubin's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, each one separately. Add vanilla and flour.
Make into dough ball.
Wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Form little marble shaped balls.
Press thumb in center.
Put jelly in center part (strawberry, black raspberry, apricot or desired flavor).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: mashed potatoes-made ahead
directions: Mash cooked potatoes.
Add other ingredients and mash again. Store in a casserole covered with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut cake
directions: Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: love bites
directions: Mix ingredients, refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll into balls.
Coat with cocoa or confectioners sugar.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate.
Enjoy.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, simmer 1 cup broth and chicken pieces until they are no longer pink.
Add the remaining broth, water and vegetables, except the peas, dill weed and black pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add the noodles or pasta and cook until the noodles or pasta are barely tender.
Stir in the peas or green beans; cook 5 minutes until the peas or beans are tender.
Serves 6.

title: country cake from scratch
directions: Stir together all ingredients in large bowl with mixer.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 45 minutes (depends on oven).

title: ice cream mexicana
directions: In small pitcher, mix Kahlua and milk.
In 4 cold glass dishes, scoop 1/4 of ice cream in each dish.
Cover with 1/4 Kahlua mix.
Top with cream and cherry.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cream oleo, flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix with mixer the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Combine pie filling with milk; pour on layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Can be served as is, as a coney sauce or over spaghetti with grated cheese, onions, beans and oyster crackers.

title: diabetic strawberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve pudding in diet Sprite which has been heated.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Freeze in
ice cream maker.
tags: Jell-O instant vanilla pudding with NutraSweet

title: quick apple delight
directions: Melt oleo in a 9-inch pie plate. Stir in sugar, flour and egg. (I just mix in pie dish.)
Stir in chopped apples and sprinkle over top with cinnamon.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve while hot topped with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 3.

title: dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars and lids.
Wash cucumbers and slice lengthwise or leave whole if small enough.
To each quart jar, add 1 teaspoon dill seed and 1 garlic bud.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Bring 2 quarts water, 1 quart vinegar and 1/2 cup salt to a boil.
Slowly pour boiling liquid into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims clean and adjust lids.
Process in a boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
These pickles will be ready to eat in about 7 to 10 days.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Place peeled and sliced apples in casserole baking dish.
Cover with sugar and nutmeg.
Dot butter on top.
Mix flour, baking powder, shortening and milk.
Spread this over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix baking soda and water together and pour over raisins; let stand overnight.
Next morning, sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in raisin mixture.
Add oil and stir well.
Batter will be thick.
Grease two 1-pound coffee cans (or small pans) and fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to 325° for 1/2 hour.
This is delicious with cream cheese served with fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken kiev
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: maple sugar cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; beat in egg.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: In large frying pan, cook chicken parts in oil until lightly browned, turning once.
Add onion; stir until cooked.
Mix broth, curry powder, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over chicken; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Turn chicken once.
Increase temperature; stir in pepper and pineapple.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in bananas. Remove chicken to a heated serving platter.
In a small bowl, mix rum and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in remaining sauce.
Cook until thickened; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cashews.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix the pudding according to directions on the box using the 6 cups of milk.
Add vanilla and sour cream to the pudding; mix well.
Pour over angel food cake that has been torn into bite size pieces and place in large dish.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar to the pie filling.
Spread over top and refrigerate.

title: mexican salad
directions: Break up lettuce into large bowl.
Add kidney beans, cheese and onion.
Prepare Ranch dressing according to package directions; add to lettuce mixture.
Mix ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle crushed chips on top and serve.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grind cheese and crackers in a food chopper.
Add pimentos. Beat eggs, slightly.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, milk and vinegar to egg mixture.
Cook in a double-boiler until light in color and thickened.
Pour over cheese, pimento and crackers.
Pour mixture into oiled vegetable ring mold, dusted lightly with fine cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly before removing from mold.
Turn out on a large platter and serve with cream cheese.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Combine soup, wine and mushrooms.
Place chicken breasts down in liquid mixture.
Add butter.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: ethella's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan, rounding edges of the mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Drain off fat once meat loaf is done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream
the
margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour and
mix
thoroughly.
Add	chips
and
nuts; mix again. Drop by teaspoon
on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15	minutes, until they are a soft honey color.
It is important not to overbake.

title: cream pie
directions: Blend and mix pudding.

title: glo's cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add cabbage and water. Cover pan. Cook until cabbage is tender-crisp. Add milk. Bring almost to boiling; remove from heat (may set pan over hot water). Add salt and pepper. Serve with crackers or croutons.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Melt butter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in bowl.
Dip biscuits in butter then cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place in glass baking dish. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Melt candy and gelatin in hot water.
Cut candy into 3 or 4 pieces each before doing this to make it easier to melt it.
Add pineapple juice and cold water to make 2 cups.
Allow to partially set.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip, celery, nuts and cherries.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunchy oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal crumbs, onion salt and pepper. Dip chicken in butter; roll in cereal crumb mixture.
Place skin sides up in an ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, until thickest pieces are done, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in oil; remove chops and season to taste.
Brown pepper and onion.
In baking dish add rice, water, vegetables and seasonings.
Mix well.
Place chops on top.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: hot dinner roll sandwiches
directions: Slice dinner rolls in half, lengthwise (do not break apart). Spread bottom layer with Dijon mustard.
Next layer 2 or 3 thin slices of ham, turkey and roast beef.
Over top of meat, put one slice of cheese until all meat is covered.
Place top layer of rolls over meat and cheese.
Put in oven at 300° until warm and cheese is melted.
This is delicious.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, eggs, pineapple, nuts and vanilla together.
Bake in greased sheet cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and butter.
Spread over cake.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except fillo dough, until well blended.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with enough milk to make a creamy dip consistency.
Add garlic salt or onion salt to taste.
Dip your favorite chips and enjoy.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts (reserve 1/4 cup nuts for top).
Place apples into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Sift (into separate bowl) dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Mix together all ingredients
and pour over apples.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix and then bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave margarine on High 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients to margarine and mix.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Beat.
Pour in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch) and cool.

title: carol cooler
directions: Mix pineapple juice, carbonated beverage and cherry juice. Pour into ice-filled glasses.
Top each with maraschino cherry.

title: pumpkin cheese ball
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, pumpkin, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder and lemon juice.
Mix well until creamy.
Cover and chill.
Shape into ball; roll in chopped pecans, if desired.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix egg, margarine and cake mix.
Press together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over dough.
Sprinkle with pecans (optional). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes without opening door.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2 in. pan or dish.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom.
Mix cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour batter over nuts and coconut.
Using mixer, cream cheese and melted butter.
Spread over top of unbaked cake batter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes or until done.

title: macadamia-oat snowballs
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy; gradually add 1/2 cup powdered sugar; beating well. Add vanilla and flour, mixing well.
Stir in oats and chopped nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan; roll balls in powdered sugar and cool on wire racks.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Pour meat mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with corn bread batter.
Spread carefully with a wet spoon.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a clean flower pot, plastic or silk flowers, gummy worms and a garden trowel.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir dry ingredients thoroughly to blend.
Mix in well.
If dough seems dry, add a drop or two of cream.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: low-fat morning glory muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix applesauce, eggs, vanilla and add dry ingredients.
Mix in apple, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Spray muffin tins with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, melted oleo and 1 egg.
Stir well.
Pat into bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 frosting and 2 eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Put caps in pan and brush with butter.
Saute onions in 2-cup measuring cup for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Add stems and cook uncovered until tender, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in bread, parsley, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put about 1 tablespoon in each cap, 12 to a plate.
Microwave at Full power 2 minutes.
Cover plate with wax paper.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all together; form a ring.
Add strawberry preserves to center of ring and place Ritz crackers around ring.

title: barbecue
directions: *I take a cloth (rag), 3 x 3-inches, and tie it together by wrapping thread around the top.

title: burrito bake
directions: Mix refried beans, Bisquick and water well and spread in 10-inch greased pie plate.
Cook ground beef or turkey until brown; drain and put on the bean mixture.
Put picante on top of the beef and spread the cheese on top of that.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: board of education raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs, flour, sugar and butter until creamy.
Add raisins, water raisins were cooked in and juice from half a lemon.
In bottom of each unbaked pie crust, put 1/4 cup flour mixture used in apple pie.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine cheese, chiles, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Heat oil and fry each tortilla for a few seconds.
Keep them limp, as overfrying wil make them hard.
Drain tortillas on paper towels.

title: cornhusker kick-off bars
directions: Combine noodles, pretzels, candies, raisins and coconut in large bowl; set aside.
Melt margarine and peanut butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Pour mixture over noodle mixture until thoroughly coated.
Press lightly into a greased jelly roll pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican party bread
directions: Slice top off the loaf of bread.
Hollow inside and break into pieces to dip later.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, chili peppers, Cheddar cheese and dried beef (cut into pieces).
Pour this filling into hollowed out bread.
Put sliced top back on and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can rinse the dried beef to take off some of the salt.
Dry well and then proceed. You can also add, if you wish, minced onion, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice the bread in half lengthwise.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients and spread on one half of the loaf.
Put the bread halves back together and wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts, in a 350° oven.

title: french toast waffles
directions: Spread bread with butter; dip in egg mixture made of eggs, milk and seasonings.
Toast in waffle iron.
Serve with butter and syrup or honey or applesauce.

title: hot cross muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt into medium bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Beat together egg, oil and evaporated milk.
Stir with wooden spoon just until flour is moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into buttered muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes. Remove from tins and cool 5 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown. Let cool. Cream next 2 ingredients and spread on cooled crust. Top with pie filling. Prepare Dream Whip as package directs. Put on top of blueberries and sprinkle with nuts. Cool in refrigerator and serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, strawberries and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 50-55 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled eggs
directions: Put eggs in single layer in saucepan.
Add enough tap water to cover eggs about 1 inch.
Quickly bring water to boiling.
Boil on medium to high heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let eggs stand covered in the hot water 10-15 minutes for large eggs. Run cold water over eggs until cooled.
To remove shell, gently tap all over.
Roll egg between the hands to loosen shell, then peel, starting at large end.
Hold egg under running cold water or dip in bowl of water to help ease off shell.

title: cherry nut nuggets(favorite)
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese.
Add sugar, egg and almond extract.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls into nuts.
Press cherry half into each ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cover slaw mixture with salt and let stand for 3 to 4 hours. Drain well.
Pour vinegar, sugar and seeds over mixture.
Mix well and freeze.

title: christmas fudge(never fail)
directions: Combine in large pan (Dutch oven type).
Bring to boil; lower heat slightly and continue to boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chocolate, margarine, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Pour into large greased pan.
This makes a lot!

title: crepes
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Beat eggs in small bowl; stir in milk.
Beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in small skillet; stir into batter.
Heat a 6 or 7-inch skillet slowly.
(Test temperature by sprinkling a few drops of water; when drops bounce about, skillet is ready.)
Lightly butter skillet.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cut half the meat from bone and brown in hot fat.
Add remaining meat and bone to cold water.
Add browned meat, onion and salt; cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and rice or barley.
Continue cooking for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: soft beef tacos
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well. Stir in water, cumin, chili powder, oregano, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: indian saggost(beef and spinach curry)
directions: Heat butter and oil in large pan.
Add onions, garlic and spices and fry over medium heat until onions are soft.
Add the meat and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned.
Stir in spinach and half the yogurt. Cover and simmer over low heat for 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Add a little water during cooking if needed.
Before serving, add remaining yogurt.
Serve with rice and mango chutney.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine first 4 items; bring to a boil, rolling.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla; cool and beat until thick.
Frost 2 layers.

title: french beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato latkes
directions: You will also need colander, a pancake turner and a frying pan.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce and place in large serving bowl.
Layer next 5 ingredients.
Cover top layer with mayonnaise.
Let set 24 hours in fridge.
Mix before serving.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except cucumbers. Chill. If more spicy taste is desired, add more vinegar, mustard, etc. Wash 2 cucumbers; cut off ends to seeds and slice in about 1/4 inch slices; pour sour cream dressing over cucumbers. Let marinate. Keep chilled and turn a couple of times. Makes a little over 1 cup. Serve on coleslaw or vegetable salad.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients 2 hours before serving.
It can be mixed ahead of time.
It keeps well.
Serve with crackers, veggies or chips.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together as you would corn bread.
Bake in hot oven at 450°.
Will make 2 skillets of bread.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery & pepper - add other ingredients and simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and cube potatoes.
Add celery and onions.
Combine Ranch dressing with mayonnaise and water.
Add to potatoes and toss to coat.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.
This is very, very good.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add beaten egg yolks, sugar and finely cut dates.
Cook about 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: copper pennies
directions: Scrape carrots; slice into thin rounds.
Cook in a small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain; cool and place in kettle.
Add other ingredients; stir and heat through (do not boil).
Pour over carrots; when cool, put in refrigerator to chill.

title: christmas icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add sugar and honey.
Beat for 10 additional minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Fold in nuts and fruit and form into rolls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in aluminum foil or heavy cellophane and store in the freezer overnight.
When ready to use, slice in 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: turkey and rice quiche
directions: Combine rice, turkey, tomato, onions, green pepper, basil, salt, ground red pepper, milk and eggs in 13 x 9-inch pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with cheeses.

title: arizona skillet dinner(heart healthy)
directions: In a large skillet, heat corn oil.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Toss with macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: laura behne's dumplings
directions: Add enough flour to other ingredients so dough does not stick to the fork.
Drop into boiling soup or chicken and noodles. Cook, uncovered, for approximately 10 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: jello mandarin orange
directions: Dissolve jellos in hot water.
Add oranges and pineapple with their juices.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Put marshmallows on top and chill.
Once chilled, mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup sour cream.
Spread over jello mixture and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: mexicorn and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Place in casserole dish.
Put Mexicorn on top of rice.
Put cream of mushroom soup next.
Top with cheese.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: In a large pot, heat oil; add cabbage and stir until cabbage is covered with oil.
Cook for 7 to 10 minutes, turning about 3 to 4 times.
Add onions, green pepper, tomatoes, water and vinegar. Mix. Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes, until almost tender.
Add smoked sausage and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook an additional 20 minutes or until done.

title: "surprise"
directions: Cook potatoes.
Make mashed or whipped potatoes.
While potatoes are cooking, brown the meat.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Drain meat of any excess grease.
Put meat in a casserole dish.
Next add corn.
Last, top with mashed potatoes and a few pats of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: granny's "squish" cake
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar and continue beating until very stiff and glossy.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into another bowl. Add oil, half the milk and vanilla in a well in the flour mixture. Beat 1 minute. Add remaining milk and egg yolks.
Beat 1 minute. Fold in egg whites.
Pour in greased and dusted 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° until done.

title: panettone(bread machine; one pound loaf)
directions: Put all ingredients into the bread case in the same way as a standard loaf and place the bread case in the main unit.
Press the mode button to select loaf and then press the start button.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, adding whole egg; blend mixture by adding enough buttermilk to make medium batter.
Pour into hot, greased (bacon drippings preferred) muffin pans.
Bake at 450° or 500° for about 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes enough for 8 muffins.

title: slaw
directions: Mix after each addition.
Combine all the above ingredients together.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo and margarine for 5 minutes in iron skillet or heavy pot.
Add soda, stirring.
Put popped corn in roaster and pour mixture over, stirring lightly.
Roast for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Popcorn breaks apart easily when cool.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and cut apples in half, then put them in a greased baking dish.
Put 1 teaspoon butter on each apple half.
Mix together the flour, sugar and cinnamon. Add enough water to make the mix "gooey."
Pour over the apples and bake at 350° until soft. Remove and place a
marshmallow on top of each (red hots are optional).
Place back in oven until melted.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add 7-Up.
Refrigerate until it begins to jell.
Add to jello mixture the bananas, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine sugar and flour in saucepan. Stir in juice and egg. Cook over low heat until thick. Take from heat and add butter.
Chill.
Fold topping into whipped cream.
Put on top of jello mixture. Cut into squares and serve.

title: apple stack cake
directions: In large cooker, cook apple until good and tender.
Mix shortening, eggs, sugar, sorghum, milk, vanilla and flour until thick, then bake in an 8-inch iron pan until done (use toothpick inserted in cake; if it comes out clean the cake is done).
There should be enough batter to make 3 cakes.
After cake is baked, cut each cake through the middle to make 6 layers.
Stack on top of each other with apples spread between each layer.
Fill each pan about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 2 cups water and salt in 2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil; stir once or twice.
Place orange peel on top of rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove and discard orange peel.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add pop; refrigerate for 5 minutes. When cake cools, punch holes all over cake.
Pour jello mixture over it.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls (approximately the size of a golf ball).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar and salt; stir.
Then add dry milk and half of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening.
Then mix in, gradually, remaining flour until consistency of dough.
Place in a greased bowl until it is doubled in bulk.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pico de gallo
directions: In food processor or blender, blend all ingredients together until desired consistency. Let set at least 1 hour before serving. Serve with your favorite chips or crackers. Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter with fork and put 1/2 of mixture into graham cracker crust.
In double boiler, mix next 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool completely.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over powdered sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover with meringue.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry and liquid ingredients alternately.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Put on 1 teaspoon of filling and cover top with 1 teaspoon of cookie mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen approximately.

title: shrimp portofino
directions: Saute butter, garlic and thyme with shrimp and broccoli until shrimp are half cooked and garlic just beginning to brown.
Add white wine and chicken stock and let simmer.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix sugar and mustard together.
Place in saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook very slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles, then continue cooking for 5 more minutes. Cool and refrigerate.
Makes quart of sauce.
Keeps well and may be frozen.
Sauce is good with fish, ham and corned beef.

title: easy chicken barbecue
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in frying pan.
Mix Coke, catsup and mustard; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour before removing cover, to let sauce thicken.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir syrup, sugar and water until sugar dissolves. When syrup boils, blend in butter.
Stir often.
Add nuts and stir constantly to hard crack stage; remove from heat.
Stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix
all together.
Put in refrigerator overnight, then eat. May add banana before serving.

title: the 2 ounce margarita
directions: Rub
a
lime
wedge
around the rim of your glass.
Dip into the coarse salt.
Mix the lime juice, tequila, Triple Sec and orange juice.
Add ice and stir until well chilled.
Pour into your
glass
with
or without ice.
If you use a blender, add enough crushed ice to make a slush.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix fat and peanut butter. Add both brown and white sugars. Beat well. Beat in eggs. Mix flour, salt and soda. Add to egg mixture. Bake 5 to 6 minutes in 425° oven.

title: meaty vegetable chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef and chicken in oil over medium-high heat.
Drain.
Add water, carrots, zucchini, tomatoes, onion, turnip and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beef is tender.
Add beans and chili sauce; simmer 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: smoky mountain pie
directions: Cream the butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spiced peach halves
directions: Drain syrup and add spices and lemon juice.
Heat and add peach halves.
Allow to cool several hours.
Strain syrup and use peaches with meat or salad.
The unused syrup can be used with peach jello for dessert or salad.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown steak in hot oil in large skillet; drain.
Return to skillet and add tomatoes, green peppers, onion, water, soy sauce, pepper, bouillon granules, garlic powder and ginger.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 55 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken kabob(serves 1)
directions: Dissolve Hi-Energy Chicken Soup Supplement in water; stir in thyme and rosemary.
Marinate chicken in this mixture for 20 minutes.
Place chicken and vegetables on toothpicks; arrange in baking dish.
Pour marinade over top; baste, then microwave for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken and vegetables; baste, then cook for about 5 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and soda, then stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: heavenly butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Add sugar and beat slowly.
Add vanilla, salt, crushed Butterfingers, Cool Whip and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into freezer.
Add milk to freezer line.
Freeze.

title: corn-tomato scallop
directions: Cream a medium size onion in butter until soft, but not brown. Add corn to onion.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 can of tomatoes. Then add corn and onion mixture.
Finish with other 1/2 of tomatoes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a medium hot oven about 35 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; reserve 3/4 stick butter.
Melt and mix with crumbs to put on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours. Very good!

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk until creamy.
Add vanilla. Stir in sifted flour and salt.
Mix well.
Spread in rectangle, about 10 x 13-inch on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
While still warm, spread with melted chocolate. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut into squares while still warm. Yields about 5 or 6 dozen.

title: bacon cheese quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 5 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese in pie shell and melt.
Sprinkle bacon pieces and onion in pie shell.
Add 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese over bacon and onion.
In a separate bowl, mix whipping cream, eggs, dill, pepper and salt with a beater.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 20 minutes until firm.

title: delicious raspberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, then bananas. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add flour to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk. Bake at 325° for about an hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: In bottom of 6 to 10-inch baking dish, spread refried beans. Brown ground beef and drain.
Put in taco seasoning and water; cook until beef is almost dry.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil 7-Up and cinnamon.
Add margarine.
Pu out biscuits and put approximately 1 tablespoon of chopped apples in center of each biscuit.
Pinch biscuit up over apples.
Place each in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour boiled mixture over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, add tapioca and apple juice to apples.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon and vanilla.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Make lattice strips from pie dough to place over top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, or until crust is brown.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets (do not use stems).
Cut cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix together first six ingredients.

title: nacho beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in a baking dish and cover with 1/2 cup tortilla chips (crushed) and shredded cheese.
Run in oven to melt cheese.

title: raisin and spice squares
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt on wax paper.
Boil raisins rapidly for 10 minutes in 2 cups water. Transfer raisins and liquid to a bowl (cool to lukewarm).
Add egg, shortening and sugar.
Add flour mixture; add nuts.
Pour in pan; bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cake that don't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, pineapple, nuts, oil, vanilla and bananas. Stir, do not beat, only a few stirs and it is mixed.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: favorite noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix next five ingredients with mayonnaise and then mix with noodles in baking dish.
Heat soup with 1/2 cup milk and melt cheese with soup.
Add to other ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, celery will be crunchy, or bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Casserole should be bubbly.
Bread crumbs can be added last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: family ground beef casserole
directions: Cook onion until lightly browned in one tablespoon hot fat. Add ground beef and brown.
Mix with cooked rice, tomatoes and seasonings.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole, top with bacon and bake at 375° until bacon is crisp, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in flour to which you have added the soda and salt.
Drop by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: aunt betty's brownies
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl; beat at medium speed until mixed, then beat at high speed for 3 minutes. Stir nuts into mixture.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375`.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Let rolls thaw.
Pat out each roll into a circle.
Place 3 or 4 slices of pepperoni and a little Mozzarella cheese on each roll. Wrap dough up around mixture to form roll.
Let raise on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: simple nutty candy
directions: In large pot,
mix sugar and syrup and stir over medium heat until sugar
is
dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Stir in corn flakes and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Move
fast
because this sets when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: taco fiesta dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sour cream, taco mix and salsa until smooth.
Spread on a 12-inch tray (such as a pizza tray). Layer the vegetables on top of the dip, finishing with the shredded cheese.
Serve with the tortilla chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar, teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg in container with tight lid. Sprinkle a few nuts in bottom of Bundt pan. Cut biscuits in quarters. Shake a few pieces at a time in sugar mixture. Layer in Bundt pan until all biscuit quarters are used. Mix melted margarine, cinnamon, brown sugar, nutmeg and nuts. Pour over top of biscuits. Bake at 375° about 20 minutes. Turn onto cake plate or aluminum foil immediately and leave for a few minutes or topping will stick. Good warm or cold. Let your guests pinch off what they want.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Put spaghetti on to cook.
In a large frypan, saute chicken in oil, stirring until done, approximately 5 minutes. Add vegetables. Cover and steam, stirring often, until crispy-tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti and teriyaki sauce. Stir until well blended.
Serves 3 or 4.
Garlic bread or toast is excellent with this.

title: quick and easy lemon pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl. Pour into 2 crusts and refrigerate.

title: ajvar
directions: Stem, de-vein, and seed bell peppers and chilies. cut into chunks. Peel eggplant and cut crosswise into 1 inch slices. Put 2/3 c. vinegar, 2 c. water and 1 Tbsp. coarse salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil, add eggplant slices. return to boil for 5 minutes. stirring, drain while you boil peppers and chilies 5 minutes using remaining 2/3 c. vinegar, 2 c. water and 1 Tbsp. salt. drain and reserve. Sizzle garlic in 1/4 c. oil for 1 minute. Place cooked, drained eggplant and pepper mix in bowl of food processor and puree. Add 1 1/2 tsp. salt and paprika. Return sauce to pan and simmer over medium heat until thickens to dipping consistency.
This is a Serbian relish great for dip or spread on crackers. Add yogurt to make a salad dressing. Freezes well.

title: great green beans
directions: Drain beans; combine in baking dish with mushrooms.
Cube cheese into 1/2-inch chunks.
Add to beans and mix well.
Dot butter over top.
Sprinkle bread or cracker crumbs over all, if desired.

title: the best chip dip!
