directions: Make this dip a day before serving to let the flavors blend well.
Shred dried beef.
Mix cream cheese with shredded dried beef and diced scallions.
Refrigerate.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pam may be used.
Bake over a pan of water to keep cake moist.
Bake 1 hour at 225°, then 1 hour at 250°, and then 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Pour off grease.
Add soup, tomatoes, beans and chili.
Let mixture come to a boil, then pour into casserole dish, alternating chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili bites
directions: Make a smooth, thick batter by adding water to the 7 ounces flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop a teaspoonful at a time into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: chicken bog
directions: Fry chickens, dipped in flour, until brown, in drippings, about 2/3 cup.
Saute pepper, onions and celery; add tomatoes and heat to boiling.
Add washed rice.
Spread evenly over bottom of roaster.
Place chicken on top.
Pour boiling water over whole dish until covered.
Place lid on roaster and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Spread pineapple evenly in bottom of dish.
Next, add blueberries.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar next; add 1/2 box cake mix. Add crushed nuts, then balance of cake mix.
Melt oleo and drizzle on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: doris' apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup butter and the cream cheese and let come to room temperature.
Add 2 cups of flour and blend well.
Chill.
Roll out half of the dough and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Reserve the remaining dough for the top crust.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour the mixture into the crust.
Roll out the remaining crust and place over the filling.
Cut slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken breasts in orange sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brown in butter in pan.
Remove.
Add flour, sugar, spices and remaining salt to drippings in pan.
Stir to a smooth (and ugly) paste.
Gradually stir in orange juice.
Cook, stirring, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add chicken.
Simmer over low heat until chicken is tender, about 20 minutes.
Serve with hot rice and sauce. Delicious!

title: orange energy booster
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a blender until smooth and frothy. Garnish with orange slice or maraschino cherry.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: herb buttered potatoes and peas
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, cook potatoes in 4 cups boiling water with salt for 15 to 18 minutes; drain.
Cut potatoes in half and add butter, salt and seasonings.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in peas; heat for 5 minutes.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to boil.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in cola.
Chill until lightly thickened.
Combine celery, pecans, cherries, pineapple and coconut, if desired.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy; add to fruit
mixture, stirring well.
Fold cream cheese mixture into gelatin; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: spicy cranberry relish
directions: Combine all; mix well and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.
Serve cold.
Yields 3 cups relish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a double boiler add the milk and butter.
In a bowl mix the eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add the flour, cocoa and salt. Combine the mixtures and cook to desired thickness.
Stir to keep creamy during the cooking.
Add the vanilla.
Place into prebaked pie shells. Cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fully
cook
sausage; drain very well. Combine sausage, onions, cheese
and
flour.
Mix well. Spread in unbaked pie
crust.
Beat
together
eggs,	milk and parsley flakes.
Slowly pour
over	sausage
mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes or until the filling is set.

title: red velvet swirl cake
directions: Beat White cake mix, egg whites, 1-1/3 c. buttermilk and vegetable oil until creamy. In a separate bowl, beat yellow cake mix,
1/2 c. buttermilk, whole egg, cocoa, soda, food coloring and vinegar until creamy.
Alternate spooning red and white batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Swirl batter gently with a knife - (do not scrape bottom of pan).
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Makes 2 bought crust or 1 deep-dish pan crust.

title: fruit crush
directions: Bring to a boil the water and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in 3 containers.
Add 1 quart 7-Up or ginger ale to each container when using.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
butter
and cook over slow heat until thick.
Add butter and cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Add milk; whip cream cheese until all dissolved.
Add nut meats.

title: falafel
directions: Sort and wash chickpeas and place in large bowl. Cover with water to 2 inches above beans. Cover and let stand for 8 hours. Drain beans. Combine chickpeas, cilantro and next 8 ingredients in a food processor until mixture resembles coarse meal. Divide chickpea mixture into 16 equal portions, shaping each into 1/2 inch thick patties. Heat 2 Tbsp. oil in a large non-stick skillet. Add 5 patties and cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Repeat procedure twice with remaining oil and patties. Spread 1 Tbsp. Yogurt-Tahini Dip in each pita half. Fill with 1 patty. Serves 8 (2 pita halves each).

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to the sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
More flour can be used to get the right texture for rolling out cookies.
Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well after each addition.
Add blackberries, juice also.
Then together add flour, soda and all spices.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or bake 55 to 60 minutes in a tube pan.
Use icing of choice.
I use cream cheese!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil.
Stir constantly, continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234° stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Cool.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and bring to a full boil. Mix biscuit mix and milk and beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth mixture.
Cook until dumplings are steamed done.

title: red snapper supreme
directions: Season the fillets
with salt and pepper.
Arrange them in a 9 x
13-inch	baking	dish
and
pour
the wine and water around them. Cover with wax paper and poach in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Remove
the
fish to a buttered oval baking dish large enough
to	hold
the
fillets
in	a single layer. Reduce pan juices to
cup.
Use big pans, lots of surface area.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Top with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes and serve with crackers or Doritos chips.

title: texas pioneer canning jar bread
directions: Wash and dry 8 pint wide-mouth jars.
Grease well.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place lids to jars in pan of water and heat.

title: crispy chicken supreme
directions: Add paprika to crushed Rice Krispies and set aside.
Beat egg and milk slightly; add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth. Dip chicken in batter and coat with Rice Krispies.

title: overnight pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain, rinse and cool.
Shred lettuce in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with macaroni.
Add ham, peas and cheese.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream, onion, mustard and pepper sauce.
Spread over casserole and seal edges.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Toss before serving.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Add other ingredients, except pecans and parsley.
Chill several hours. Shape into ball; roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Combine sour cream and soda in separate container.
Blend together.
Add flour, poppy seed and flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in ungreased angel food cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Check in 15 minutes.
If too brown on outside, turn heat to 325° for remainder of hour. Invert pan to cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil the sugar, water and cinnamon together and then add the juices.
Color with red food coloring.
Mix equal parts with hot water to serve.

title: sugar free spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tightly sealed jar. Use approximately 1 teaspoon in boiling water for each serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar.
Don't beat hard, just blend.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake in two 8-inch pans, greased and floured.

title: ken stuff casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers.
Add ground beef and brown well; drain.
Add Veg-All, corn and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes with top on pan.
Remove from heat.
Add Minute rice. Stir, cover and let set 5 minutes before removing cover.
May sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add sugar, flour and milk together; mix water and cocoa together.
Pour all ingredients together.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until thick.
For real smooth pudding, beat with mixer a little when finished cooking. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, one cup of pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into three well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with one cup pecans.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on the package.
Pour a little of the salad dressing into the bowl and swirl around.
Add some pasta, followed by some of the mixture of vegetables, crabmeat, cheese and dressing.
Add the remaining pasta and other ingredients.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese (and garlic salt or powder, if desired).
Cover and chill before serving. Enjoy!

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
In saucepan, blend together soup, milk and cheese; heat and stir until melted.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer except crust.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Chill and serve with your favorite fruit topping.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: hungarian lattice pastry
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder into a bowl.
Add butter and mix as for pie dough.
Mix together sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add this mixture to dough mixture and mix well.
Dough will be soft.
Roll a little more than 1/2 of dough into a jelly roll pan.
Spread the jam on top.
Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar gradually until stiff, then fold in nuts.
Spread the nut mixture on the preserves.
Be careful not to mix the two toppings. Make narrow strips of dough in a crisscross pattern on top of nut filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes through cake with fork.
Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 c. coconut in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer one minute.
Spoon carefully over cake, allowing to soak through holes.
Cool completely.
Fold Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: devil burgers
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl and spread it evenly on one-half of a hamburger roll.
Then broil for 5 to 10 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, drain and chop broccoli.
Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: disappearing hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend together well and put in pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.
Watch it disappear.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Reserve salmon liquid.
Add milk to make 1 cup.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings and water in large kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook approximately 1 hour.
During the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking time, chopped cabbage or 1 cup of frozen peas can be added.

title: cheese ball with everything
directions: Let Swiss and Cheddar cheeses come to room temperature.
In a large mixer bowl, beat together softened cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Beat in Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, undrained pimiento, pickle relish, half of the bacon, half of the pecans, salt and pepper.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls; place on waxed paper.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add the buttermilk, butter, honey, salt, baking soda, wheat germ and 4 cups flour; mix well. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto a heavily floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and water.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve with whipped cream.

title: low-fat spaghetti
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan with nonstick spray.
Add the ground turkey or chicken, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and veggies are tender. Drain.

title: morea's mouth-watering chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter until golden.
Remove and place in baking dish.
Lightly saute mushrooms, as many as you wish, green pepper, water chestnuts and seasonings.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Heat the can of soup diluted with the wine.
Pour over chicken and bake, covered, 25 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake another 25 minutes.
This dish can be prepared in advance and baked when ready to serve.
Enjoy!

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut and apples.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk; blend.
Add eggs and blend.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: microwave chicken and dumplings
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place chicken, water, onion, celery, carrots, salt and pepper; cover.
Microwave at Medium-high for 15 minutes.
Stir together cornstarch and water; add to chicken mix. Cover and microwave at Medium-high for 10 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Spoon on dumplings around edge of dish. Microwave at Medium-high 5 to 6 minutes, covered, until puffed and not doughy.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham crumbs and melted margarine. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 glass dish. Refrigerate. In bowl, mix powdered sugar, softened margarine and the eggs until silky, about 5 minutes. Spread on graham crust. Layer with sliced bananas and drained pineapple. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with strawberries or cherries. Sprinkle on nuts and drizzle with chocolate syrup if you like. Enjoy.

title: squash chicken
directions: Cook fryer on top of stove until medium-done.
Pour over squash.
Let it cook until chicken and squash are done.
Add the spices.
Let it cook about twenty more minutes.
Stir once in a while.

title: chocolate cinnamon drink
directions: Bring water and cinnamon candies to a boil over medium-high heat in medium saucepan, stirring until candies melt.
Add milk; whisk in drink mix.
Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Pour into mugs.
Serve warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Dip sliced tomatoes in mixture and fry in small amount of oil until golden brown.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add hot water, sugar, lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Add 12 ounces Cool Whip to gelatine mixture.
Cut cake into about 1-inch squares.
Place cake in bottom of pan.
Cover with gelatine mixture.
Add layers until cake and gelatine mixture are used. Press firmly with back of spoon.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, ice with remaining box of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut. Decorate with cherries, if desired.

title: chocolate raspberry crumb bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and salt until all mixed.
With floured fingers, press 1 3/4 cups crumb mixture onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; reserve remaining mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: green delight salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in 7 cups boiling water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Set aside to congeal.

title: microwave caramel popcorn balls(yields 12 balls)
directions: Combine caramels, water and butter in 1-quart casserole dish. Heat in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir halfway through heating.
Pour over popcorn, tossing lightly, to coat evenly.
Grease or moisten hands and form mixture into balls.

title: whipped cream fruit salad
directions: Chil thoroughly bowl, beaters and cream.
Prepare fruit. Whip cream; fold in fruit.
Ready to eat.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix butter, flour and salt in a bowl and microwave for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in milk. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring every minute until thick.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.

title: beef and potatoes casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of an 8 x 12-inch casserole. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Combine browned ground beef, broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and chopped tomato. Place on top of potatoes. Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture. Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
(You can substitute frozen peas instead of the broccoli.)

title: microwave beef stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers and remove seeds.
Wash peppers. Combine egg, 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce and next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and place peppers in a lightly greased 8-inch baking dish.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes giving dish a half turn after 6 minutes.
Spoon a small amount of remaining spaghetti sauce over tops of peppers; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat remaining spaghetti sauce and serve with peppers.
Serves 4.

title: orange honey muffins
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and soda.
Add salt and stir in oats.
Add dry ingredients to last four well blended ingredients but stir just until mixed.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water until mixed.
Boil to 250°, then add butter and peanuts.
Cook and stir almost constantly to 290° to 300°.
Remove from stove; work and pull until hard.

title: saucy cubed steak
directions: In a nonstick skillet, sprayed with cooking spray, brown steak on both sides, searing in juices.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle over top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease	and
flour
two
(9-inch) baking pans.	In large bowl with
electric
mixer
at
low
speed, beat flour, sugar, mayonnaise, milk, egg, soda, cinnamon, salt, cloves and nutmeg, 2 minutes,
scraping bowl often.
(Batter will be thick.) Stir in apples
with
spoon, also raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter in pans. Bake
at
for 45 minutes or until tester in center comes out
clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove; cool, fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer, skin side up in a shallow roasting pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Follow directions on pie crust.
Brown chicken; mix potato soup and milk, then put chicken and soup mix in pie crust, then add seasonings.
Put top crust on.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: *I used a combo of Monterey Jack, Cheddar and Mozzarella.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Use juice and water to equal 3 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Pour into dish and add cherries and pineapple.
Chill.

title: cookies and cream icing
directions: Fold crumbs in cool whip.
Great on chocolate cake.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, vinegar, sugar and oil. Pour over carrots, pepper and onion. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Grease a casserole dish with oleo.
Place macaroni in dish, then add all other ingredients.
Mix together well.
Put a sprinkle of bread crumbs on top and dot with a few pieces of oleo.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dressing balls
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine. Pour over dried bread cubes. Add 2 eggs. Pour in broth. Sprinkle with poultry seasoning and salt. Stir well.
When slightly cooled enough to handle, form into approximately 20 balls (size of small orange) or use 1/2-cup ice cream dipper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Melt shortening in skillet, adding the 4 onions thinly sliced. Saute the onions over low heat.
Add the beef, stirring lightly until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly on low temperature for 2 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: braided easter bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and salt.
Continue beating. Add dissolved yeast and milk, lemon rind, fruit, vanilla, butter and some flour. Knead on floured board, working in enough flour so dough is not sticky.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover with wet towel. Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.

title: thick strawberry whip
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients in order listed; blend until smooth.
If desired, garnish with reserved strawberries.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Mixture stays thick and creamy in the refrigerator.

title: anita's rolls
directions: Pour 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add 2 packages yeast and heat 1 cup water to boiling.
Add 1 cup Crisco, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add 2 eggs to yeast mixture, then add Crisco mixture.
When cool, add 6 cups flour; stir well.
Allow to rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Pat down and put in fridge.
Put in muffin tins to rise as needed.
When you put rolls in muffin tins, let rise 1 hour, then bake at 375° until brown.

title: flake candy
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and cream in a saucepan and cook to soft ball form stage.
Mix with the corn flakes, rice cereal, peanuts and coconut.
Put in a buttered pan, cool and cut.

title: pumpkin chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl combine eggs, sugar, pumpkin and vegetable oil.
Beat until smooth, set aside.
In a large bowl sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Slowly add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture, stirring well.
Fold in chocolate or butterscotch chips.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups with batter until three-fourths full.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes or until centers of muffins bounce back when touched.
Makes approximately 36 muffins.
Can also be made as mini-muffins.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak together for 15 minutes the molasses, milk and All-Bran. Add the beaten egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: christmas eve casserole(mix on christmas even to pop in oven on christmas morning.)
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put bread in the bottom. Sprinkle on cheese, then sausage and ham.
Beat up eggs with milk (2 cups) and pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over just before baking. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marshmallows creme fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir ingredients until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Allow to cool and cut as desired.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, spices and molasses.
Add milk, soda and flour; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Let set.
Melt oleo. Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pour melted oleo over batter and sprinkle sugar mixture over oleo.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Smash tomatoes by squeezing through fingers.
Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix apple and baking soda; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves together; add to butter mixture.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased, floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Freezes well.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix well and add lemon jello, mixed with warm water.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan (test to be sure done).
Pierce with fork after removing from oven.
Mix juice of lemons and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake.
This makes a glaze.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine margarine and sugar; add eggs and salt.
Alternate adding flour, cornmeal and milk.
Lastly add soda dissolved in boiling water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the top of the pie has puffed up like a souffle.
Center will still be shaky when pie is taken from oven.
Do not overbake.

title: country style ribs
directions: Mother made some delicious country style ribs.
She seared the ribs in electric skillet until brown.
Then added water and steamed for a good while.
She added salt, pepper, barbecue sauce and a tad of brown sugar.
Water, if needed, and simmer until very tender, like 2 hours.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Toast noodles, seeds and nuts in butter.
Drain and set aside. Prepare bok choy.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until it begins to set. Fold in peaches.
Turn into a 3-quart mold or a dish.
Chill until firm.
In top of double boiler, combine peach juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool. Fold in cream cheese and whipped cream.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Spread on gelatin; sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Put pretzels and butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until butter is melted.
Remove from oven to cool. Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese; let set up.
Make box of Jell-O according to directions; let set up in refrigerator for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: hurricane chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Place in small mixing bowl. Add sugar and water at the same time and beat until blended.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Add butter a little at a time.
Beat after each additional until smooth.
Add vanilla. Frosting for 2 layers.

title: pralines
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan. In it, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, corn syrup and milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until sugars dissolve and mixture boils. Cook to soft-ball stage (234°), stirring occasionally. Cool 10 minutes. Add vanilla. Beat by hand 2 minutes. Add pecan halves; beat until mixture loses its gloss. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. If candy becomes too stiff to drop, add a tablespoon or so of hot water. Makes 16.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Beat together first 11 ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat at high for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cakes test done. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Place bottom layer on cake plate; spread Cream Filling evenly over layer.
Add top layer; drizzle warm Creamy Chocolate Glaze over cake; sift powdered sugar lightly over it and press down lightly with spoon.
(Before putting on the powdered sugar, place a fancy paper doily on top of layer.)
Lift off doily gently so design will not be disturbed.
Refrigerate any leftover cake. Makes 1 cake, 10 to 16 servings.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pans or use paper liners. Sift and measure flour into large bowl.
Measure all spices; add to flour.
Measure remaining dry ingredient and add to flour. Stir dry ingredients.
Add oil, applesauce and egg.
Mix to blend. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Flour meat and brown in small amount of shortening.
Add onion and garlic.
Let meat cook until almost done.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Stir often.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate chip-nut pie
directions: Mix ingredients (in order listed).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: For a Family of Four:
Fry each pork chop until brown on both sides.
Place in deep baking dish.
Chop up the onion and spread in dish.
Drain all but 1 cup of peas; spread in dish.
Take last cup of peas; with the water and all, spread in dish.
Pour the tomato soup over the top.
Cook in oven until bubbling or chops are tender at 350°.

title: never fail chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan, side by side.
Put 1 slice of cheese on each breast.
Prepare sauce using soup and wine.
Pour over chicken, then put Stove Top stuffing mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour melted butter over the top and return to oven for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Beat until thick and spread into a 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.
Top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until onions are golden.

title: roasted nachos
directions: In a small pan, cook red pepper, onion and jalapenos until soft.
Place chips on ovenproof platter with refried beans. Arrange vegetables, cheese and black olives.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, remove skin and bones from chicken breasts; cut breast meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In a cup, mix vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, water, salt and pepper.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Increase heat to medium-high; add chicken.
Cook, stirring, until chicken loses pink color (5 minutes).
To chicken in skillet, add frozen peas, pineapple chunks with juice and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hog's head cheese
directions: Remove eyes and brains from head and split head in half.
Wash and scrape head thoroughly, removing excess fat.
Singe pig feet; wash and scrape.
Singe, wash and clean ears with hot water.

title: homestyle meat loaf(makes its own gravy.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, onion and pepper.
(Work the mixture as little as possible, as overworked meat becomes quite tough.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, eggs and salt. Separately, stir mushroom soup until smooth.
Blend in water.
Put 1/4 cup of soup mixture into meat; mix well.
Brown meatballs and pour in soup.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: egg sausage scramble
directions: Cook and stir sausage until done; drain.
Place sausage in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and milk; mix in cheese.
Pour mixture over sausage; sprinkle with croutons.
Bake uncovered at 325° for about 1 hour (until clean knife inserted into center comes out clean).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels; mix with butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until thoroughly mixed. Fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzels.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Let set 10 minutes. Stir well and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of the nuts.
Roll cheese ball in 1/2 cup nuts.

title: sweet-tart franks for a crowd
directions: In
a
quart casserole, stir together jelly and mustard. Microwave
on High for 1 to 2 minutes until mixture can be stirred smooth.
Cut
franks into 1-inch pieces and add to jelly mixture, stirring to coat each piece.
Cover.
Microwave on High 4 go 6 minutes (stirring after 2 minutes) until franks are hot.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, cook, peel and grate.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container. Use 2 to 3 teaspoons for each cup of boiling water.

title: glazed burton beets
directions: Drain 1 1/2 cups beet juice into medium saucepan.
Add packets of sugar substitute to beet juice; stir.
Add 6 teaspoons cornstarch to 1/2 cup water and stir until dissolved, and all lumps are gone.
Pour cornstarch mixture into beet juice.
Cook on medium-high until beet mixture boils and gets thickened.
Add cinnamon and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Add drained beets and stir until heated through.
Even kids like this one!
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Slowly stir in reserved pineapple juice; add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Put into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine oleo and crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes - 30.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
